[Amit Varma]: If you love cricket, you'll love Crick Heroes.

01:38:49.080 --> 01:38:50.880
[Amit Varma]: And I had discovered this technique

01:38:51.080 --> 01:38:52.880
[Amit Varma]: where by squeezing it a lot

01:38:53.080 --> 01:38:54.880
[Amit Varma]: and releasing it just as, you know,

01:38:55.080 --> 01:38:56.880
[Amit Varma]: whatever I could impart great forward spin,

01:38:57.080 --> 01:38:58.880
[Amit Varma]: which made it really fast, right?

01:38:59.080 --> 01:39:01.880
[Amit Varma]: So Dravid came over once to play with us

01:39:02.080 --> 01:39:02.880
[Amit Varma]: and I bowled him.

01:39:03.080 --> 01:39:04.880
[Amit Varma]: My first ball, I was trying, you know,

01:39:05.080 --> 01:39:06.880
[Amit Varma]: kind of a backward spin kind of thing.

01:39:07.080 --> 01:39:07.880
[Amit Varma]: And that was a wide.

01:39:08.080 --> 01:39:09.880
[Amit Varma]: Next two balls, he was clean bowled.

01:39:10.080 --> 01:39:11.880
[Amit Varma]: In exasperation, he called me Shoaib Akhtar

01:39:12.080 --> 01:39:13.880
[Amit Varma]: and said, I can't play against you.

01:39:14.080 --> 01:39:16.880
[Amit Varma]: But the irony was that it was all finger spin.

01:39:16.880 --> 01:39:18.680
[Amit Varma]: There was no chucking involved.

01:39:18.880 --> 01:39:20.680
[Amit Varma]: But leaving that aside

01:39:20.880 --> 01:39:22.680
[Amit Varma]: and in case I gave the impression

01:39:22.880 --> 01:39:23.680
[Amit Varma]: that I also play cricket,

01:39:23.880 --> 01:39:25.680
[Amit Varma]: I'd be absolutely useless in a field.

01:39:25.880 --> 01:39:28.680
[Amit Varma]: So kind of moving on from your cricketing career,

01:39:28.880 --> 01:39:30.680
[Amit Varma]: like one of the things that I'm actually excited

01:39:30.880 --> 01:39:32.680
[Amit Varma]: talking about is this next part

01:39:32.880 --> 01:39:35.680
[Amit Varma]: because I have been thinking a lot in recent months

01:39:35.880 --> 01:39:37.680
[Amit Varma]: about creators in general,

01:39:37.880 --> 01:39:39.680
[Amit Varma]: about things like teaching,

01:39:39.880 --> 01:39:41.680
[Amit Varma]: about things like how do you achieve excellence

01:39:41.880 --> 01:39:42.680
[Amit Varma]: in what you do?

01:39:42.880 --> 01:39:44.680
[Amit Varma]: And there are just so many dimensions

01:39:44.680 --> 01:39:47.480
[Amit Varma]: to things that you've done in this period

01:39:47.680 --> 01:39:49.480
[Amit Varma]: in terms of writing,

01:39:49.680 --> 01:39:51.480
[Amit Varma]: in terms of starting a YouTube channel

01:39:51.680 --> 01:39:52.480
[Amit Varma]: and making that work,

01:39:52.680 --> 01:39:53.480
[Amit Varma]: in terms of coaching

01:39:53.680 --> 01:39:54.480
[Amit Varma]: and not just coaching cricket,

01:39:54.680 --> 01:39:56.480
[Amit Varma]: but also coaching sports journalism

01:39:56.680 --> 01:39:59.480
[Amit Varma]: and in terms of doing commentary

01:39:59.680 --> 01:40:01.480
[Amit Varma]: in two different languages.

01:40:01.680 --> 01:40:03.480
[Amit Varma]: So let's start with what actually came first,

01:40:03.680 --> 01:40:04.480
[Amit Varma]: which I don't know.

01:40:04.680 --> 01:40:07.480
[Amit Varma]: So, you know, after your cricketing career was done,

01:40:07.680 --> 01:40:08.480
[Amit Varma]: you know, where did you go next?

01:40:08.680 --> 01:40:09.480
[Amit Varma]: What happened next?

01:40:09.680 --> 01:40:10.480
[Amit Varma]: How were you thinking

01:40:10.680 --> 01:40:12.480
[Amit Varma]: of what you want to do from now on?

01:40:12.480 --> 01:40:15.280
[Guest]: So writing came first

01:40:15.480 --> 01:40:17.280
[Guest]: and it happened in parallel

01:40:17.480 --> 01:40:18.280
[Guest]: with kind of the second half

01:40:18.480 --> 01:40:19.280
[Guest]: of my cricket career.

01:40:19.480 --> 01:40:21.280
[Guest]: There was this,

01:40:21.480 --> 01:40:24.280
[Guest]: like, since school,

01:40:24.480 --> 01:40:26.280
[Guest]: okay, so maybe I should go

01:40:26.480 --> 01:40:28.280
[Guest]: a little further back.

01:40:28.480 --> 01:40:30.280
[Guest]: When I was in,

01:40:30.480 --> 01:40:31.280
[Guest]: like I said,

01:40:31.480 --> 01:40:33.280
[Guest]: I changed schools at one point.

01:40:33.480 --> 01:40:35.280
[Guest]: The first school that I was in

01:40:35.480 --> 01:40:38.280
[Guest]: where we were living with the joint family

01:40:38.480 --> 01:40:39.280
[Guest]: was a convent.

01:40:39.480 --> 01:40:40.280
[Guest]: And, you know,

01:40:40.280 --> 01:40:42.280
[Guest]: it is this fairly prestigious convent,

01:40:42.480 --> 01:40:44.080
[Guest]: this really old school,

01:40:44.280 --> 01:40:46.080
[Guest]: which has been around since my parents' time.

01:40:46.280 --> 01:40:47.080
[Guest]: My mother went to that school.

01:40:47.280 --> 01:40:49.080
[Guest]: My father went to the school next to it,

01:40:49.280 --> 01:40:50.080
[Guest]: which is a boys' convent.

01:40:50.280 --> 01:40:52.080
[Amit Varma]: Which school was this?

01:40:52.280 --> 01:40:53.080
[Guest]: St. Joseph's.

01:40:53.280 --> 01:40:54.080
[Guest]: Okay.

01:40:54.280 --> 01:40:56.080
[Guest]: St. Joseph's Pashan,

01:40:56.280 --> 01:40:58.080
[Guest]: and next door is Loyola's,

01:40:58.280 --> 01:40:59.080
[Guest]: where my father went

01:40:59.280 --> 01:41:01.080
[Guest]: and St. Joseph's was where my mother went.

01:41:01.280 --> 01:41:03.080
[Guest]: And they wanted me to get admission.

01:41:03.280 --> 01:41:04.080
[Guest]: And, you know,

01:41:04.280 --> 01:41:07.080
[Guest]: the whole convent colonial obsession

01:41:07.280 --> 01:41:09.080
[Guest]: with their language,

01:41:09.080 --> 01:41:10.880
[Guest]: you know, you should be able to speak good English

01:41:11.080 --> 01:41:11.880
[Guest]: from nursery,

01:41:12.080 --> 01:41:13.880
[Guest]: otherwise you won't get admission kind of situation,

01:41:14.080 --> 01:41:15.880
[Guest]: created an environment at home

01:41:16.080 --> 01:41:17.880
[Guest]: where we were speaking a lot of English.

01:41:18.080 --> 01:41:20.880
[Guest]: So despite being a Marathi family,

01:41:21.080 --> 01:41:22.880
[Guest]: despite being a family where,

01:41:23.080 --> 01:41:23.880
[Guest]: you know,

01:41:24.080 --> 01:41:26.880
[Guest]: my grandparents had most of their education in Marathi,

01:41:27.080 --> 01:41:28.880
[Guest]: we were speaking a lot of English at home,

01:41:29.080 --> 01:41:31.880
[Guest]: mainly to get me into the habit of speaking in English

01:41:32.080 --> 01:41:33.880
[Guest]: so I would fit into a convent school.

01:41:34.080 --> 01:41:35.880
[Guest]: Due to that fact,

01:41:36.080 --> 01:41:37.880
[Guest]: I've always had good English speaking skills.

01:41:37.880 --> 01:41:39.680
[Guest]: So therefore,

01:41:39.880 --> 01:41:42.680
[Guest]: I always enjoyed English throughout school.

01:41:42.880 --> 01:41:44.680
[Guest]: And when I,

01:41:44.880 --> 01:41:46.680
[Guest]: and I tried my hand at kind of writing

01:41:46.880 --> 01:41:48.680
[Guest]: throughout school, you know,

01:41:48.880 --> 01:41:50.680
[Guest]: small limericks, poems,

01:41:50.880 --> 01:41:52.680
[Guest]: not going to compete with your level of limericks,

01:41:52.880 --> 01:41:54.680
[Guest]: but the point being that

01:41:54.880 --> 01:41:57.680
[Guest]: I was dabbling around with the written form

01:41:57.880 --> 01:41:59.680
[Guest]: before I ever conceived,

01:41:59.880 --> 01:42:00.680
[Guest]: could conceive that, you know,

01:42:00.880 --> 01:42:02.680
[Guest]: I might make a living from it.

01:42:02.880 --> 01:42:05.680
[Guest]: So I had this fondness for writing

01:42:05.680 --> 01:42:08.480
[Guest]: even though I had never actually written much.

01:42:08.680 --> 01:42:11.480
[Guest]: But during my years in Mumbai,

01:42:11.680 --> 01:42:13.480
[Guest]: I actually started writing blog.

01:42:13.680 --> 01:42:15.480
[Guest]: I started writing a blog

01:42:15.680 --> 01:42:19.480
[Guest]: and would write about pretty much anything that came to me.

01:42:19.680 --> 01:42:22.480
[Guest]: Some of my oldest entries were,

01:42:22.680 --> 01:42:25.480
[Guest]: you know, what we would now identify as listicles,

01:42:25.680 --> 01:42:29.480
[Guest]: vague philosophical ramblings on, you know,

01:42:29.680 --> 01:42:32.480
[Guest]: the meaning of sport and winning and losing

01:42:32.680 --> 01:42:34.480
[Guest]: and that kind of stuff.

01:42:34.480 --> 01:42:37.280
[Guest]: Eventually, I started writing about cricket also,

01:42:37.480 --> 01:42:39.280
[Guest]: started writing about cricket more frequently,

01:42:39.480 --> 01:42:44.280
[Guest]: started a separate blog just for my writing on cricket.

01:42:44.480 --> 01:42:46.280
[Guest]: So the previous blog could have been anything,

01:42:46.480 --> 01:42:48.280
[Guest]: book reviews, song reviews,

01:42:48.480 --> 01:42:50.280
[Guest]: you know, what this song meant to me, that kind of stuff.

01:42:50.480 --> 01:42:53.280
[Guest]: But this blog was more about

01:42:53.480 --> 01:42:55.280
[Guest]: what I was thinking about the game.

01:42:55.480 --> 01:42:57.280
[Guest]: I discovered Twitter around that time,

01:42:57.480 --> 01:43:00.280
[Guest]: probably 2013, 13-ish,

01:43:00.480 --> 01:43:02.280
[Guest]: and discovered that, you know,

01:43:02.280 --> 01:43:06.080
[Guest]: there are people abroad who are dedicated women's cricket writers

01:43:06.280 --> 01:43:09.080
[Guest]: and are writing blogs about their women's cricket

01:43:09.280 --> 01:43:11.080
[Guest]: so as to give it more and more attention

01:43:11.280 --> 01:43:13.080
[Guest]: and that kind of things.

01:43:13.280 --> 01:43:15.080
[Guest]: And I thought, hey, that's something I can do.

01:43:15.280 --> 01:43:18.080
[Guest]: I can, you know, write blogs about domestic cricket,

01:43:18.280 --> 01:43:20.080
[Guest]: which no one ever talks about and no one ever covers.

01:43:20.280 --> 01:43:22.080
[Guest]: Everyone knows Jhulan Goswami, everyone knows Mithali Raj.

01:43:22.280 --> 01:43:24.080
[Guest]: Okay, fine, good.

01:43:24.280 --> 01:43:27.080
[Guest]: By now, you know, BCCI has taken over women's cricket

01:43:27.280 --> 01:43:29.080
[Guest]: and these people are slightly more famous

01:43:29.280 --> 01:43:31.080
[Guest]: than they were maybe 10 years ago.

01:43:31.080 --> 01:43:32.880
[Guest]: But domestic cricket, no one talks about us.

01:43:33.080 --> 01:43:35.880
[Guest]: So I started doing reviews of tournaments

01:43:36.080 --> 01:43:37.880
[Guest]: or, you know, previews of the season.

01:43:38.080 --> 01:43:39.880
[Guest]: I started writing that kind of stuff on my blog

01:43:40.080 --> 01:43:41.880
[Guest]: and putting it up on Twitter.

01:43:42.080 --> 01:43:43.880
[Guest]: Eventually, someone picked it up.

01:43:44.080 --> 01:43:45.880
[Guest]: Vision India reached out saying that

01:43:46.080 --> 01:43:47.880
[Guest]: we would like you to write for us.

01:43:48.080 --> 01:43:51.880
[Guest]: And at that time, I was, like, so absolutely naive.

01:43:52.080 --> 01:43:54.880
[Guest]: Zero idea about how to have conversations about money.

01:43:55.080 --> 01:43:58.880
[Guest]: I wrote my first probably 10-odd articles for them.

01:43:59.080 --> 01:43:59.880
[Guest]: Didn't even ask for any money.

01:43:59.880 --> 01:44:01.680
[Guest]: And later, you know, the good people at Vision India

01:44:01.880 --> 01:44:02.680
[Guest]: reached out to me,

01:44:02.880 --> 01:44:06.680
[Guest]: Hey, have you received your payment for this kind of thing?

01:44:06.880 --> 01:44:08.680
[Guest]: Like, no, no, no, no, I haven't.

01:44:08.880 --> 01:44:12.680
[Guest]: So that was happening in parallel while I was playing cricket.

01:44:12.880 --> 01:44:17.680
[Guest]: My blog for Vision India ran in that period.

01:44:17.880 --> 01:44:21.680
[Guest]: I was actually writing some kind of anti-BCCI stuff.

01:44:21.880 --> 01:44:23.680
[Guest]: I mean, I don't mean to be anti-BCCI,

01:44:23.880 --> 01:44:24.680
[Guest]: but I was writing about, you know,

01:44:24.880 --> 01:44:25.680
[Guest]: how women's cricket has changed,

01:44:25.880 --> 01:44:27.680
[Guest]: some for the better and some for the worse,

01:44:27.880 --> 01:44:28.680
[Guest]: while I was playing.

01:44:28.680 --> 01:44:31.480
[Guest]: Which is kind of, yeah, which is kind of,

01:44:31.680 --> 01:44:33.480
[Guest]: I didn't even, like I said, I was just so naive

01:44:33.680 --> 01:44:35.480
[Guest]: that I never even appreciated

01:44:35.680 --> 01:44:37.480
[Guest]: that there may be consequences for this kind of thing.

01:44:37.680 --> 01:44:39.480
[Guest]: Also, because it was such a small thing,

01:44:39.680 --> 01:44:43.480
[Guest]: I was like, no chance anyone of import is actually reading this.

01:44:43.680 --> 01:44:44.480
[Guest]: So it's okay.

01:44:44.680 --> 01:44:46.480
[Guest]: And then I was finding a sense of satisfaction

01:44:46.680 --> 01:44:48.480
[Guest]: and purpose through that.

01:44:48.680 --> 01:44:51.480
[Guest]: Because again, like I said, you know,

01:44:51.680 --> 01:44:52.480
[Guest]: everyone can do coaching,

01:44:52.680 --> 01:44:54.480
[Guest]: but very few people were actually,

01:44:54.680 --> 01:44:55.480
[Guest]: very few cricketers.

01:44:55.680 --> 01:44:56.480
[Guest]: I don't think anyone else.

01:44:56.480 --> 01:44:59.280
[Guest]: I may be wrong, but I don't think anyone else

01:44:59.480 --> 01:45:01.280
[Guest]: was actually writing about the game

01:45:01.480 --> 01:45:02.280
[Guest]: while they were playing the game.

01:45:02.480 --> 01:45:03.280
[Guest]: And in this sense,

01:45:03.480 --> 01:45:06.280
[Guest]: I was kind of being inspired in a way

01:45:06.480 --> 01:45:08.280
[Guest]: by what was going on in other countries

01:45:08.480 --> 01:45:10.280
[Guest]: where, you know, blogging about niche game

01:45:10.480 --> 01:45:14.280
[Guest]: is a very big and mainstream thing in its own right.

01:45:14.480 --> 01:45:17.280
[Guest]: There will be any, pick any like niche game.

01:45:17.480 --> 01:45:20.280
[Guest]: And I don't know why chess is coming to mind.

01:45:20.480 --> 01:45:22.280
[Guest]: I don't want to say chess right now.

01:45:22.480 --> 01:45:25.280
[Guest]: But lawn bowls.

01:45:25.280 --> 01:45:29.080
[Guest]: I'm sure there are very active blogs about lawn bowls

01:45:29.280 --> 01:45:31.080
[Guest]: and very active communities about lawn bowls in,

01:45:31.280 --> 01:45:33.080
[Guest]: for example, maybe Australia.

01:45:33.280 --> 01:45:37.080
[Guest]: So I was kind of following the leads of these kind of communities

01:45:37.280 --> 01:45:40.080
[Guest]: and writing and putting my stuff out on Twitter

01:45:40.280 --> 01:45:42.080
[Guest]: and finding that, oh, this is interesting.

01:45:42.280 --> 01:45:44.080
[Guest]: So after I quit,

01:45:44.280 --> 01:45:47.080
[Guest]: like having no plan when I quit,

01:45:47.280 --> 01:45:50.080
[Guest]: but after I quit, one of the first things that I did was

01:45:50.280 --> 01:45:53.080
[Guest]: I reached out to some people within the media saying that,

01:45:53.080 --> 01:45:54.880
[Guest]: hey, this is what I've done before.

01:45:55.080 --> 01:45:57.880
[Guest]: Would you be interested in hosting these kind of articles?

01:45:58.080 --> 01:45:58.880
[Guest]: And they said yes.

01:45:59.080 --> 01:46:02.880
[Guest]: And they said, OK, we'll pay you X amount of money for each article

01:46:03.080 --> 01:46:05.880
[Guest]: and you write X amount of articles per month.

01:46:06.080 --> 01:46:08.880
[Guest]: I was like, oh, I can make some money here.

01:46:09.080 --> 01:46:10.880
[Guest]: It was not a lot of money, but it was,

01:46:11.080 --> 01:46:12.880
[Guest]: I had never been able to conceive that, you know,

01:46:13.080 --> 01:46:14.880
[Guest]: I might be able to support myself financially

01:46:15.080 --> 01:46:16.880
[Guest]: or even start of supporting myself financially

01:46:17.080 --> 01:46:18.880
[Guest]: through writing about cricket.

01:46:19.080 --> 01:46:19.880
[Guest]: I think this is cool.

01:46:20.080 --> 01:46:21.880
[Guest]: And so I started writing about cricket.

01:46:21.880 --> 01:46:23.680
[Guest]: I started discovering that, you know,

01:46:23.880 --> 01:46:25.680
[Guest]: rather than just writing from home,

01:46:25.880 --> 01:46:28.680
[Guest]: you can travel and cover tournaments.

01:46:28.880 --> 01:46:31.680
[Guest]: And there is something called accreditation

01:46:31.880 --> 01:46:34.680
[Guest]: where you become an actual member of the media

01:46:34.880 --> 01:46:36.680
[Guest]: when you gain that accreditation,

01:46:36.880 --> 01:46:39.680
[Guest]: which is basically a pass for a media person

01:46:39.880 --> 01:46:41.680
[Guest]: to cover a particular tournament.

01:46:41.880 --> 01:46:45.680
[Guest]: And then this very interesting little journey happened

01:46:45.880 --> 01:46:47.680
[Guest]: before the accreditation.

01:46:47.880 --> 01:46:49.680
[Guest]: No, actually, at that point,

01:46:49.680 --> 01:46:55.480
[Guest]: I had received accreditation and covered a 2016 T20 World Cup,

01:46:55.680 --> 01:46:57.480
[Guest]: covered a couple of women's games in that tournament.

01:46:57.680 --> 01:46:59.480
[Guest]: So that was my first ever assignment

01:46:59.680 --> 01:47:02.480
[Guest]: as a written journalist, you know,

01:47:02.680 --> 01:47:03.480
[Guest]: where I'm actually at the ground.

01:47:03.680 --> 01:47:04.480
[Guest]: I'm in a press box.

01:47:04.680 --> 01:47:06.480
[Guest]: Oh, so this is what a press box is like.

01:47:06.680 --> 01:47:08.480
[Guest]: You know, the heroes have kind of changed.

01:47:08.680 --> 01:47:11.480
[Guest]: Rather than wanting to run into Jhulan Goswami,

01:47:11.680 --> 01:47:13.480
[Guest]: I'm running into Osman Samiuddin.

01:47:13.680 --> 01:47:15.480
[Guest]: Oh, my God, I read his work.

01:47:15.680 --> 01:47:16.480
[Guest]: He's sitting right here.

01:47:16.680 --> 01:47:17.480
[Guest]: That is so cool.

01:47:17.480 --> 01:47:20.280
[Guest]: Those kind of moments I'm having.

01:47:20.480 --> 01:47:23.280
[Guest]: Then I have this little bit of a journey.

01:47:23.480 --> 01:47:27.280
[Guest]: The women's Big Bash has begun.

01:47:27.480 --> 01:47:30.280
[Guest]: Indians are going to be playing in it for the first time.

01:47:30.480 --> 01:47:32.280
[Guest]: Harbin Preet Kaur and Smriti Mandana.

01:47:32.480 --> 01:47:35.280
[Guest]: I figure I have a few friends in Australia.

01:47:35.480 --> 01:47:37.280
[Guest]: There are going to be Indians in Australia.

01:47:37.480 --> 01:47:41.280
[Guest]: There's going to be no one else really covering it from India.

01:47:41.480 --> 01:47:46.280
[Guest]: Why don't I travel and see if I can cover this tournament

01:47:46.280 --> 01:47:48.080
[Guest]: on my own, like totally freelance.

01:47:48.280 --> 01:47:49.080
[Guest]: Reached out to a few people saying,

01:47:49.280 --> 01:47:51.080
[Guest]: hey, will you guys be interested in articles?

01:47:51.280 --> 01:47:53.080
[Guest]: It was nowhere near, you know,

01:47:53.280 --> 01:47:55.080
[Guest]: the cost of covering my trip.

01:47:55.280 --> 01:47:57.080
[Guest]: It was still going to be significantly out of pocket.

01:47:57.280 --> 01:48:00.080
[Guest]: But at the same time, because I was able to live with friends,

01:48:00.280 --> 01:48:03.080
[Guest]: I wasn't really incurring as much cost as I might have.

01:48:03.280 --> 01:48:05.080
[Guest]: And I went to Australia for a couple of months.

01:48:05.280 --> 01:48:07.080
[Guest]: And I went to Brisbane.

01:48:07.280 --> 01:48:08.080
[Guest]: I went to Melbourne.

01:48:08.280 --> 01:48:10.080
[Guest]: I went to Sydney.

01:48:10.280 --> 01:48:15.080
[Guest]: And I just experienced that tournament as a journalist.

01:48:15.080 --> 01:48:16.880
[Guest]: I wasn't writing about it every day.

01:48:17.080 --> 01:48:18.880
[Guest]: But I would go to every game.

01:48:19.080 --> 01:48:19.880
[Guest]: I would sit in the designated area,

01:48:20.080 --> 01:48:21.880
[Guest]: which is called, which is, you know,

01:48:22.080 --> 01:48:22.880
[Guest]: what they pass for a press box.

01:48:23.080 --> 01:48:24.880
[Guest]: Because these are small community games.

01:48:25.080 --> 01:48:27.880
[Guest]: The WBBL is not as big a tournament as it was before.

01:48:28.080 --> 01:48:30.880
[Guest]: I also happen to be around at the same time

01:48:31.080 --> 01:48:32.880
[Guest]: the Australian Open is being played.

01:48:33.080 --> 01:48:35.880
[Guest]: So I visit the Australian Open for the first time.

01:48:36.080 --> 01:48:40.880
[Guest]: So there is this exposure to a wider sporting experience

01:48:41.080 --> 01:48:43.880
[Guest]: and a different culture, a culture in the country,

01:48:43.880 --> 01:48:48.680
[Guest]: which is sports mad, which really,

01:48:48.880 --> 01:48:51.680
[Guest]: which really, I wouldn't say it was like a pivotal moment,

01:48:51.880 --> 01:48:53.680
[Guest]: but it was a moment of broadening of my horizons.

01:48:53.880 --> 01:48:54.680
[Guest]: Because I'd been to Australia before.

01:48:54.880 --> 01:48:56.680
[Guest]: I'd been to Australia three times as a player.

01:48:56.880 --> 01:48:58.680
[Guest]: But you're a player, you're staying in a hotel,

01:48:58.880 --> 01:48:59.680
[Guest]: you're going from a team bus,

01:48:59.880 --> 01:49:01.680
[Guest]: you're going to a ground, coming back from a team bus,

01:49:01.880 --> 01:49:03.680
[Guest]: you're coming back here far, you know,

01:49:03.880 --> 01:49:06.680
[Guest]: at most you're going to a little bit of sightseeing at the end of it.

01:49:06.880 --> 01:49:09.680
[Guest]: Whereas here I was mapping out my own directions,

01:49:09.880 --> 01:49:11.680
[Guest]: budgeting my own trip,

01:49:11.680 --> 01:49:14.480
[Guest]: figuring out what my travel schedule should be,

01:49:14.680 --> 01:49:16.480
[Guest]: booking my own flights.

01:49:16.680 --> 01:49:19.480
[Guest]: The entire experience was just so educational.

01:49:19.680 --> 01:49:22.480
[Guest]: And in terms of opening up,

01:49:22.680 --> 01:49:25.480
[Guest]: the WBPL is like one of the best run women's leagues in the world.

01:49:25.680 --> 01:49:27.480
[Guest]: So opening up to the possibilities of, you know,

01:49:27.680 --> 01:49:29.480
[Guest]: what women's cricket holds,

01:49:29.680 --> 01:49:32.480
[Guest]: that was a brilliant experience.

01:49:32.680 --> 01:49:36.480
[Guest]: And I still have no idea how I actually conceived of it

01:49:36.680 --> 01:49:38.480
[Guest]: and actually went ahead and did it.

01:49:38.480 --> 01:49:41.480
[Guest]: If I think about it now, I don't know if I'll do that.

01:49:41.680 --> 01:49:44.280
[Guest]: But yeah, it was just such a new experience.

01:49:44.480 --> 01:49:49.280
[Guest]: At every step I'm discovering literally something new.

01:49:49.480 --> 01:49:52.280
[Guest]: For example, there are separate cycling tracks in Australia

01:49:52.480 --> 01:49:54.280
[Guest]: for only cyclists.

01:49:54.480 --> 01:49:56.280
[Guest]: You know, the small, small things which blow your mind.

01:49:56.480 --> 01:50:01.280
[Guest]: Or the fact that the trails here are so well marked.

01:50:01.480 --> 01:50:03.280
[Guest]: Or the cricket here is so well done.

01:50:03.480 --> 01:50:05.280
[Guest]: You know, they have a Christmas party.

01:50:05.480 --> 01:50:07.280
[Guest]: Christmas, of course, in Australia, it's summer.

01:50:07.280 --> 01:50:10.080
[Guest]: So they have a summer Christmas party on the ground

01:50:10.280 --> 01:50:13.080
[Guest]: where after the match they open up the ground for the audience

01:50:13.280 --> 01:50:15.080
[Guest]: and they have a band in the middle of the stadium

01:50:15.280 --> 01:50:18.080
[Guest]: and everyone's playing Christmas carols on a cricket ground.

01:50:18.280 --> 01:50:21.080
[Guest]: These are the kind of experiences which I would never have gotten

01:50:21.280 --> 01:50:23.080
[Guest]: if I had not gone on that kind of trip.

01:50:23.280 --> 01:50:27.080
[Guest]: And that was probably the first beginnings of my life

01:50:27.280 --> 01:50:30.080
[Guest]: as a writer, as a sports journalist,

01:50:30.280 --> 01:50:34.080
[Guest]: as a member of the written press, so to speak.

01:50:34.080 --> 01:50:39.880
[Guest]: But, yeah, almost exploring this sporting landscape

01:50:40.080 --> 01:50:41.880
[Guest]: in a way I had never done before.

01:50:42.080 --> 01:50:44.880
[Guest]: As a player, the view is always very bracketed.

01:50:45.080 --> 01:50:46.880
[Guest]: It's always very narrow.

01:50:47.080 --> 01:50:48.880
[Guest]: And here I was trying to go as wide as I could.

01:50:49.080 --> 01:50:50.880
[Amit Varma]: Yeah, that's fascinating.

01:50:51.080 --> 01:50:52.880
[Amit Varma]: And you kind of brought back memories of my own

01:50:53.080 --> 01:50:56.880
[Amit Varma]: because I remember in 2006 I really wanted to cover India to Pakistan.

01:50:57.080 --> 01:50:59.880
[Amit Varma]: And the typical way of doing that was

01:51:00.080 --> 01:51:02.880
[Amit Varma]: that you get a freelance gig with an English newspaper

01:51:02.880 --> 01:51:04.680
[Amit Varma]: because that covers your cost.

01:51:04.880 --> 01:51:06.680
[Amit Varma]: So I got a gig writing pieces for The Guardian

01:51:06.880 --> 01:51:09.680
[Amit Varma]: and I did some small audio thing for the BBC while I was there.

01:51:09.880 --> 01:51:12.680
[Amit Varma]: And my whole thing was I just want to cover the cost of this tour.

01:51:12.880 --> 01:51:14.680
[Amit Varma]: So it wasn't even like make a profit.

01:51:14.880 --> 01:51:16.680
[Amit Varma]: Just cover the cost. You want to go, you want to watch the cricket,

01:51:16.880 --> 01:51:18.680
[Amit Varma]: you want to soak in the experience.

01:51:18.880 --> 01:51:20.680
[Amit Varma]: So I kind of totally get that.

01:51:20.880 --> 01:51:26.680
[Amit Varma]: I'm curious about craft here because, you know, one of the...

01:51:26.880 --> 01:51:28.680
[Amit Varma]: And I don't want to embarrass you with praise,

01:51:28.880 --> 01:51:30.680
[Amit Varma]: but, you know, where you are as a writer

01:51:30.680 --> 01:51:32.480
[Amit Varma]: and sort of your work over the last year,

01:51:32.680 --> 01:51:34.480
[Amit Varma]: you don't get there overnight.

01:51:34.680 --> 01:51:35.480
[Amit Varma]: You don't get there.

01:51:35.680 --> 01:51:37.480
[Amit Varma]: You know, it takes many, many years.

01:51:37.680 --> 01:51:40.480
[Amit Varma]: Like, I look back on my own sort of progression as a cricket writer

01:51:40.680 --> 01:51:42.480
[Amit Varma]: or many of the young writers that I've worked with

01:51:42.680 --> 01:51:44.480
[Amit Varma]: that, you know, when you're young,

01:51:44.680 --> 01:51:46.480
[Amit Varma]: you're trying so hard to impress.

01:51:46.680 --> 01:51:49.480
[Amit Varma]: Sometimes you're overdoing the style, so on and so forth.

01:51:49.680 --> 01:51:51.480
[Amit Varma]: It takes time for you to find your voice,

01:51:51.680 --> 01:51:53.480
[Amit Varma]: to find the confidence, to find that...

01:51:53.680 --> 01:51:55.480
[Amit Varma]: where you can just sit back and do what you have to do.

01:51:55.680 --> 01:51:59.480
[Amit Varma]: So, you know, how did that craft evolve in your case?

01:51:59.480 --> 01:52:02.280
[Amit Varma]: Because I like... I have to apologize and say

01:52:02.480 --> 01:52:05.280
[Amit Varma]: I haven't read your earlier pieces from when you started writing.

01:52:05.480 --> 01:52:07.280
[Amit Varma]: I've just read what you've done over the last year or so.

01:52:07.480 --> 01:52:08.280
[Amit Varma]: And it's fantastic.

01:52:08.480 --> 01:52:10.280
[Amit Varma]: And there's one quality that I noted in your work

01:52:10.480 --> 01:52:12.280
[Amit Varma]: that cuts across not just your writing,

01:52:12.480 --> 01:52:13.280
[Amit Varma]: but also your YouTube work,

01:52:13.480 --> 01:52:16.280
[Amit Varma]: which is that you're not trying to impress.

01:52:16.480 --> 01:52:18.280
[Amit Varma]: It's very straightforward.

01:52:18.480 --> 01:52:19.280
[Amit Varma]: It is what it is.

01:52:19.480 --> 01:52:22.280
[Amit Varma]: There's no added artifice to that, you know.

01:52:22.480 --> 01:52:25.280
[Amit Varma]: So is that, again, something that is kind of natural?

01:52:25.480 --> 01:52:28.280
[Amit Varma]: Is there a moment where you say that

01:52:28.280 --> 01:52:30.080
[Amit Varma]: you kind of have to work at that moment,

01:52:30.280 --> 01:52:32.080
[Amit Varma]: if you get what I'm saying?

01:52:32.280 --> 01:52:33.080
[Amit Varma]: So I'm very curious,

01:52:33.280 --> 01:52:35.080
[Amit Varma]: like you did my writing course as well, for example.

01:52:35.280 --> 01:52:38.080
[Amit Varma]: You're clearly a person who wants to get as much

01:52:38.280 --> 01:52:41.080
[Amit Varma]: sort of exposure to different aspects of craft

01:52:41.280 --> 01:52:42.080
[Amit Varma]: and thinking about writing.

01:52:42.280 --> 01:52:45.080
[Amit Varma]: Take me a little bit through that journey of yours.

01:52:45.280 --> 01:52:47.080
[Guest]: I think to answer this question,

01:52:47.280 --> 01:52:48.080
[Guest]: I need to go back to my childhood.

01:52:48.280 --> 01:52:50.080
[Amit Varma]: Please do, yeah, let's go back.

01:52:51.280 --> 01:52:54.080
[Guest]: And I need to go back to...

01:52:54.080 --> 01:52:57.880
[Guest]: I mean, my dad used to make regular trips to Mumbai at the time.

01:52:58.080 --> 01:53:00.880
[Guest]: And we had this custom that,

01:53:01.080 --> 01:53:02.880
[Guest]: you know, whenever he comes back from Mumbai,

01:53:03.080 --> 01:53:05.880
[Guest]: the first question my younger brother and I would ask him,

01:53:06.080 --> 01:53:06.880
[Guest]: what you got for us?

01:53:07.080 --> 01:53:09.880
[Guest]: You know, he has to come back and he has to bring us a gift.

01:53:10.080 --> 01:53:12.880
[Guest]: So, which still in our family is called

01:53:13.080 --> 01:53:14.880
[Guest]: the what you got for us gift.

01:53:15.080 --> 01:53:16.880
[Guest]: And very often those would be books.

01:53:17.080 --> 01:53:18.880
[Guest]: Very often you would bring back

01:53:19.080 --> 01:53:20.880
[Guest]: your Nancy Drews and your Hardy Boys.

01:53:20.880 --> 01:53:24.680
[Guest]: There was no end of Enid Blyton's

01:53:24.880 --> 01:53:26.680
[Guest]: littered around my childhood.

01:53:26.880 --> 01:53:29.680
[Guest]: There was this memory of

01:53:29.880 --> 01:53:33.680
[Guest]: spending so many months reading Lord of the Rings

01:53:33.880 --> 01:53:35.680
[Guest]: and our entire family was reading it.

01:53:35.880 --> 01:53:37.680
[Guest]: And it would be, you know, this,

01:53:37.880 --> 01:53:39.680
[Guest]: it would just be situated in our bathroom

01:53:39.880 --> 01:53:42.680
[Guest]: because unfortunately, we have a lot of people

01:53:42.880 --> 01:53:44.680
[Guest]: who used to read while in the toilet.

01:53:44.880 --> 01:53:47.680
[Guest]: And it is this kind of

01:53:47.680 --> 01:53:52.480
[Guest]: maybe just an extension of that environment where English was emphasized at a young age.

01:53:52.680 --> 01:53:55.480
[Guest]: Therefore, reading was also emphasized at a young age.

01:53:55.680 --> 01:53:57.480
[Guest]: And I read exclusively fiction at the time.

01:53:57.680 --> 01:53:59.480
[Guest]: I found non-fiction boring.

01:53:59.680 --> 01:54:02.480
[Guest]: And it is interesting, recently someone put out a

01:54:02.680 --> 01:54:04.480
[Guest]: quote on Twitter saying that, you know,

01:54:04.680 --> 01:54:06.480
[Guest]: non-fiction greater than fiction.

01:54:06.680 --> 01:54:08.480
[Guest]: I was like, yeah, maybe.

01:54:08.680 --> 01:54:11.480
[Guest]: I mean, non-fiction might be what

01:54:11.680 --> 01:54:13.480
[Guest]: what I read now and what I find really, you know,

01:54:13.680 --> 01:54:16.480
[Guest]: helps me level up in whatever I'm doing.

01:54:16.480 --> 01:54:20.280
[Guest]: But I spent my entire childhood reading exclusively fiction,

01:54:20.480 --> 01:54:22.280
[Guest]: reading like fantasy,

01:54:22.480 --> 01:54:24.280
[Guest]: a little bit of sci-fi here and there.

01:54:24.480 --> 01:54:28.280
[Guest]: And maybe that's what ingrained a sense of storytelling in me

01:54:28.480 --> 01:54:30.280
[Guest]: because I didn't, like I said,

01:54:30.480 --> 01:54:33.280
[Guest]: I did a BSc after my graduation.

01:54:33.480 --> 01:54:35.280
[Guest]: I played cricket for 15 years.

01:54:35.480 --> 01:54:38.280
[Guest]: I have no formal education in writing.

01:54:38.480 --> 01:54:40.280
[Guest]: My education is just my childhood,

01:54:40.480 --> 01:54:43.280
[Guest]: my experiences, the fact that I like to read

01:54:43.480 --> 01:54:45.280
[Guest]: and once in a while will, you know,

01:54:45.280 --> 01:54:48.080
[Guest]: take the effort of reading an autobiography.

01:54:48.280 --> 01:54:51.080
[Guest]: And those are the kind of books that interested me at the time.

01:54:51.280 --> 01:54:54.080
[Guest]: So the evolution of the craft definitely

01:54:54.280 --> 01:54:56.080
[Guest]: starts from the reading habit,

01:54:56.280 --> 01:54:58.080
[Guest]: which is just a part of my childhood.

01:54:58.280 --> 01:55:01.080
[Guest]: And again, unconsciously has helped me in

01:55:01.280 --> 01:55:04.080
[Guest]: being a writer and being someone who is able to

01:55:04.280 --> 01:55:07.080
[Guest]: make a living from writing today.

01:55:07.280 --> 01:55:09.080
[Guest]: And beyond that,

01:55:09.280 --> 01:55:12.080
[Guest]: I remember reading a lot.

01:55:12.280 --> 01:55:14.080
[Guest]: Like I said, that phase when I discovered Twitter

01:55:14.080 --> 01:55:16.880
[Guest]: and suddenly discovered, oh, there's so much to read.

01:55:17.080 --> 01:55:18.880
[Guest]: And I suddenly discovered that there are so many

01:55:19.080 --> 01:55:22.880
[Guest]: writers who write about cricket and think about cricket.

01:55:23.080 --> 01:55:26.880
[Guest]: And like I said, they have from the media

01:55:27.080 --> 01:55:29.880
[Guest]: a very different background and a very different view.

01:55:30.080 --> 01:55:32.880
[Guest]: And me as a player, I'm reading that view.

01:55:33.080 --> 01:55:35.880
[Guest]: And suddenly I think, oh, their view is so much,

01:55:36.080 --> 01:55:38.880
[Guest]: I wouldn't say wider or larger, but just different.

01:55:39.080 --> 01:55:41.880
[Guest]: It's just so different as someone in the media

01:55:41.880 --> 01:55:44.680
[Guest]: and someone as a writer and really good pieces

01:55:44.880 --> 01:55:46.680
[Guest]: of cricket writing at the time.

01:55:46.880 --> 01:55:49.680
[Guest]: And again, most of my reading has been restricted to cricket.

01:55:49.880 --> 01:55:51.680
[Guest]: And this is something I'm consciously trying to do nowadays,

01:55:51.880 --> 01:55:53.680
[Guest]: is read more about other sports and whatnot.

01:55:53.880 --> 01:55:55.680
[Guest]: But at the time, Osman Samiuddin,

01:55:55.880 --> 01:55:57.680
[Guest]: Andrew Fidel Fernando,

01:55:57.880 --> 01:56:01.680
[Guest]: Jared Kimbers writing some really funny, irreverent stuff.

01:56:01.880 --> 01:56:05.680
[Guest]: All those are kind of probably influencing that.

01:56:05.880 --> 01:56:08.680
[Guest]: Very early on, I remembered this or I discovered this quote,

01:56:08.680 --> 01:56:12.480
[Guest]: which is copy technique, not style.

01:56:12.680 --> 01:56:13.480
[Guest]: And I actually started doing that.

01:56:13.680 --> 01:56:16.480
[Guest]: I was like, OK, this person has written this nice piece.

01:56:16.680 --> 01:56:18.480
[Guest]: What technique are they using here?

01:56:18.680 --> 01:56:21.480
[Guest]: Not consciously, but unconsciously.

01:56:21.680 --> 01:56:24.480
[Guest]: I wasn't actually trying to name the technique.

01:56:24.680 --> 01:56:26.480
[Guest]: I was just trying to say, OK, can I write a piece

01:56:26.680 --> 01:56:29.480
[Guest]: which is something similar to what this person is writing?

01:56:29.680 --> 01:56:32.480
[Guest]: And, you know, for the longest part,

01:56:32.680 --> 01:56:35.480
[Guest]: I had no idea what these official journalistic terms were.

01:56:35.680 --> 01:56:37.480
[Guest]: I had no idea what an opinion piece was.

01:56:37.480 --> 01:56:41.280
[Guest]: I had no idea the difference between a feature and a report,

01:56:41.480 --> 01:56:42.280
[Guest]: and a reported piece.

01:56:42.480 --> 01:56:44.280
[Guest]: I had no idea what a newspeg was.

01:56:44.480 --> 01:56:46.280
[Guest]: Again, these are words that I discovered

01:56:46.480 --> 01:56:48.280
[Guest]: when I kind of got into the field

01:56:48.480 --> 01:56:53.280
[Guest]: and I had to kind of overcome my ignorance and ask,

01:56:53.480 --> 01:56:55.280
[Guest]: what is a newspeg?

01:56:55.480 --> 01:56:57.280
[Guest]: And, you know, those are the kind of things,

01:56:57.480 --> 01:56:58.280
[Guest]: those are the ways I learned.

01:56:58.480 --> 01:57:01.280
[Guest]: Being a freelancer had its advantages

01:57:01.480 --> 01:57:05.280
[Guest]: in terms of being kind of on the outside

01:57:05.280 --> 01:57:08.080
[Guest]: and not being insulated into any one environment.

01:57:08.280 --> 01:57:11.080
[Guest]: At the same time, I missed out, I think,

01:57:11.280 --> 01:57:16.080
[Guest]: on these constant exposure to these really good writers,

01:57:16.280 --> 01:57:20.080
[Guest]: which I think sometimes being in an organization gives you.

01:57:20.280 --> 01:57:22.080
[Guest]: But, and it is funny, I mean,

01:57:22.280 --> 01:57:24.080
[Guest]: in the process of building out my sports journalism course,

01:57:24.280 --> 01:57:27.080
[Guest]: I read out, I went back and read a few of my pieces.

01:57:27.280 --> 01:57:31.080
[Guest]: And some of the pieces were like, yeah, OK, good, honest effort.

01:57:31.280 --> 01:57:33.080
[Guest]: Some of the pieces were actually good.

01:57:33.080 --> 01:57:35.880
[Guest]: I picked up some old pieces as examples of, you know,

01:57:36.080 --> 01:57:37.880
[Guest]: writing that I had done, which worked well

01:57:38.080 --> 01:57:39.880
[Guest]: and which kind of still holds up.

01:57:40.080 --> 01:57:42.880
[Guest]: So I wouldn't call it talent,

01:57:43.080 --> 01:57:45.880
[Guest]: but I would call it a culmination of the environment

01:57:46.080 --> 01:57:47.880
[Guest]: where A, English was emphasized,

01:57:48.080 --> 01:57:49.880
[Guest]: B, reading was emphasized,

01:57:50.080 --> 01:57:52.880
[Guest]: C, education was kind of emphasized.

01:57:53.080 --> 01:57:56.880
[Guest]: And then add into that my unique experiences in sport,

01:57:57.080 --> 01:58:00.880
[Guest]: allowing me to kind of bring a viewpoint that others didn't

01:58:00.880 --> 01:58:04.680
[Guest]: and therefore kind of giving me a point of difference in,

01:58:04.880 --> 01:58:06.680
[Guest]: you know, amongst so many other bloggers.

01:58:06.880 --> 01:58:08.680
[Guest]: No one was writing about women's domestic cricket.

01:58:08.880 --> 01:58:11.680
[Guest]: No one was writing about, well, not no one,

01:58:11.880 --> 01:58:13.680
[Guest]: but very few people were writing about women's cricket.

01:58:13.880 --> 01:58:15.680
[Guest]: So therefore, when someone wrote about it,

01:58:15.880 --> 01:58:17.680
[Guest]: even if it wasn't written really well,

01:58:17.880 --> 01:58:19.680
[Guest]: people read it and people shared it.

01:58:19.880 --> 01:58:24.680
[Guest]: And even if it is just like a report piece on just providing information,

01:58:24.880 --> 01:58:26.680
[Guest]: people read, people shared it.

01:58:26.680 --> 01:58:31.480
[Guest]: And therefore I got a little bit of a following on social media.

01:58:31.680 --> 01:58:35.480
[Guest]: But honestly, it's only in the process of building out

01:58:35.680 --> 01:58:38.480
[Guest]: this post-journalism course that I have really thought about

01:58:38.680 --> 01:58:40.480
[Guest]: what makes me a good writer,

01:58:40.680 --> 01:58:42.480
[Guest]: what works, what doesn't work,

01:58:42.680 --> 01:58:44.480
[Guest]: what are the things I tend to use,

01:58:44.680 --> 01:58:46.480
[Guest]: what are the writing devices I tend to use more,

01:58:46.680 --> 01:58:51.480
[Guest]: what has contributed to how I have progressed as a writer so far.

01:58:51.480 --> 01:58:57.280
[Guest]: Also, one other non-craft thing that is an essential element,

01:58:57.480 --> 01:59:00.280
[Guest]: I think, of why I have succeeded as a writer

01:59:00.480 --> 01:59:03.280
[Guest]: is being brave in terms of what I write.

01:59:03.480 --> 01:59:07.280
[Guest]: Because, you know, I'm constantly almost towing that line,

01:59:07.480 --> 01:59:10.280
[Guest]: being someone who is in the cricketing system,

01:59:10.480 --> 01:59:13.280
[Guest]: but also sometimes having to criticize that same system.

01:59:13.480 --> 01:59:17.280
[Guest]: But when in doubt, unlike, like I said,

01:59:17.280 --> 01:59:22.080
[Guest]: my evolution as a person over the last few years has

01:59:22.280 --> 01:59:25.080
[Guest]: reflected in my professional work as well,

01:59:25.280 --> 01:59:29.080
[Guest]: where I have more often than not silenced that inner doubt

01:59:29.280 --> 01:59:34.080
[Guest]: and been brave and tried to tell my truth,

01:59:34.280 --> 01:59:36.080
[Guest]: if not the truth as I see it.

01:59:36.280 --> 01:59:39.080
[Guest]: Those are actually two words which I try to remind myself of,

01:59:39.280 --> 01:59:41.080
[Guest]: you know, courage and truth

01:59:41.280 --> 01:59:46.080
[Guest]: are two things that I want to use in the content that I create.

01:59:46.080 --> 01:59:50.880
[Amit Varma]: You mentioned coaching and like one of the things I realized

01:59:51.080 --> 01:59:52.880
[Amit Varma]: after I taught my writing course for a while,

01:59:53.080 --> 01:59:56.880
[Amit Varma]: that it in a subtle way changed the way I looked at my own past writing as well,

01:59:57.080 --> 01:59:59.880
[Amit Varma]: where perhaps unlike you, I mean, I might like some of my earlier work,

02:00:00.080 --> 02:00:01.880
[Amit Varma]: but a lot of my earlier work were like cringemax.

02:00:02.080 --> 02:00:03.880
[Amit Varma]: Like, what is this? What am I doing?

02:00:04.080 --> 02:00:06.880
[Amit Varma]: I tell my students not to do this and I'm doing the exact same thing.

02:00:07.080 --> 02:00:10.880
[Amit Varma]: And it just kind of sharpened the way I look at my own writing

02:00:11.080 --> 02:00:13.880
[Amit Varma]: and sort of has that been a process with you

02:00:13.880 --> 02:00:16.680
[Amit Varma]: through your multiple sort of coaching strengths,

02:00:16.880 --> 02:00:18.680
[Amit Varma]: like, or rather your coaching lanes,

02:00:18.880 --> 02:00:20.680
[Amit Varma]: like one lane, of course, is sports journalism and writing.

02:00:20.880 --> 02:00:22.680
[Amit Varma]: There's another lane, which is cricket,

02:00:22.880 --> 02:00:26.680
[Amit Varma]: where I was going through a bunch of your fabulous videos on batting.

02:00:26.880 --> 02:00:30.680
[Amit Varma]: Right. And it's so intricate and so detailed and all of that.

02:00:30.880 --> 02:00:33.680
[Amit Varma]: And do you sometimes wish that you had been coached

02:00:33.880 --> 02:00:36.680
[Amit Varma]: at the start of your career by someone like you?

02:00:36.880 --> 02:00:40.680
[Guest]: Oh, yeah, absolutely. I mean, half of the expression

02:00:40.680 --> 02:00:44.480
[Guest]: through the content right now is that, you know,

02:00:44.680 --> 02:00:47.480
[Guest]: this information is now available.

02:00:47.680 --> 02:00:49.480
[Guest]: Take it. Do something with it.

02:00:49.680 --> 02:00:52.480
[Guest]: Yes. I mean, having had a career where, you know,

02:00:52.680 --> 02:00:57.480
[Guest]: didn't really have this one fixed coach moving from influence to other influence.

02:00:57.680 --> 02:01:01.480
[Guest]: It's not been the driving motivation of what I do,

02:01:01.680 --> 02:01:03.480
[Guest]: but it's been a part of that.

02:01:03.680 --> 02:01:06.480
[Guest]: It's been, you know, the thrill of being able to share this.

02:01:06.680 --> 02:01:09.480
[Guest]: And rather than in a cricket academy,

02:01:09.480 --> 02:01:13.280
[Guest]: it being learned, for example, the cricket coaching videos

02:01:13.480 --> 02:01:15.280
[Guest]: in a cricket academy, 50 people learning it

02:01:15.480 --> 02:01:19.280
[Guest]: or maybe 20 people learning it, the 50,000 people learning it.

02:01:19.480 --> 02:01:24.280
[Guest]: That was a revolution in terms of, you know, the power of YouTube.

02:01:24.480 --> 02:01:28.280
[Guest]: And I was lucky, fairly lucky enough that I could discover that power

02:01:28.480 --> 02:01:33.280
[Guest]: pretty much accidentally and fairly early on in the whole creative journey.

02:01:33.480 --> 02:01:35.280
[Guest]: In terms of the writing part, yes, absolutely.

02:01:35.280 --> 02:01:40.080
[Guest]: Like I said, I've really started thinking about my writing now.

02:01:40.280 --> 02:01:44.080
[Guest]: And therefore, I've tried to reverse engineer my own process,

02:01:44.280 --> 02:01:45.080
[Guest]: which is instinctive.

02:01:45.280 --> 02:01:49.080
[Guest]: Until now, I would just put words on the page

02:01:49.280 --> 02:01:52.080
[Guest]: and then, you know, try and refine them.

02:01:52.280 --> 02:01:55.080
[Guest]: It's a very crude process, but a very instinctive process.

02:01:55.280 --> 02:01:59.080
[Guest]: A process kind of also driven in large part by emotion

02:01:59.280 --> 02:02:03.080
[Guest]: because very often I'm not someone who's employed to write every day.

02:02:03.080 --> 02:02:04.880
[Guest]: So therefore, I write when I feel like it.

02:02:05.080 --> 02:02:09.880
[Guest]: And I have that, you know, again, a lucky situation where I have that.

02:02:10.080 --> 02:02:12.880
[Guest]: So I was usually writing from a place of emotion.

02:02:13.080 --> 02:02:14.880
[Guest]: I'm angry about this. I'm sad about this.

02:02:15.080 --> 02:02:17.880
[Guest]: I'm happy about this. Wonderful match played.

02:02:18.080 --> 02:02:20.880
[Guest]: Oh, this could have been better. I wish this was different.

02:02:21.080 --> 02:02:24.880
[Guest]: Those kind of things usually came across in my writing.

02:02:25.080 --> 02:02:26.880
[Guest]: And maybe that's one point of connect

02:02:27.080 --> 02:02:30.880
[Guest]: and one point of, you know, why it has connected with so many people.

02:02:30.880 --> 02:02:34.680
[Guest]: But in terms of the actual process now,

02:02:34.880 --> 02:02:37.680
[Guest]: after having built out that course,

02:02:37.880 --> 02:02:41.680
[Guest]: after having created a process which other people can take

02:02:41.880 --> 02:02:45.680
[Guest]: and, you know, you can apply it to yourself and see if it works for you.

02:02:45.880 --> 02:02:47.680
[Guest]: Now I follow that process.

02:02:47.880 --> 02:02:51.680
[Guest]: Now I sit down and I go through my own processes

02:02:51.880 --> 02:02:53.680
[Guest]: and see if I've met my own checklists

02:02:53.880 --> 02:02:56.680
[Guest]: because this is literally how I've, you know,

02:02:56.880 --> 02:02:59.680
[Guest]: it's absolutely like how a cricketer will

02:02:59.680 --> 02:03:02.480
[Guest]: identify that this is your process,

02:03:02.680 --> 02:03:04.480
[Guest]: results and processes, we talk about it.

02:03:04.680 --> 02:03:07.480
[Guest]: When your hand comes this close to your ear,

02:03:07.680 --> 02:03:09.480
[Guest]: the ball goes on off stump line.

02:03:09.680 --> 02:03:12.480
[Guest]: When you tick X, Y, Z boxes in writing,

02:03:12.680 --> 02:03:17.480
[Guest]: the piece is likely to come out better, cleaner, clearer,

02:03:17.680 --> 02:03:19.480
[Guest]: like you constantly emphasize.

02:03:19.680 --> 02:03:23.480
[Guest]: And therefore, that is something that I follow now.

02:03:23.680 --> 02:03:26.480
[Guest]: Whereas before it was very instinctive.

02:03:26.480 --> 02:03:29.480
[Guest]: And like a year ago, if you had asked me how you do it,

02:03:29.680 --> 02:03:31.280
[Guest]: I would not have been able to tell you.

02:03:31.480 --> 02:03:33.280
[Guest]: I would just like, I write when I'm angry.

02:03:33.480 --> 02:03:35.280
[Guest]: That's what I would have said.

02:03:35.480 --> 02:03:38.280
[Amit Varma]: A good reason to write among other reasons.

02:03:38.480 --> 02:03:42.280
[Amit Varma]: So, you know, one of the things that I kind of talk about in my course

02:03:42.480 --> 02:03:45.280
[Amit Varma]: and I also draw a cricket metaphor from it

02:03:45.480 --> 02:03:49.280
[Amit Varma]: is mindful learning and learning that you're just kind of taking by osmosis.

02:03:49.480 --> 02:03:51.280
[Amit Varma]: So a lot of cricket learning is mindful.

02:03:51.480 --> 02:03:54.280
[Amit Varma]: If you go in the nets for the first time,

02:03:54.280 --> 02:03:57.080
[Amit Varma]: you know, the way your feet are moving, your elbow,

02:03:57.280 --> 02:04:00.080
[Amit Varma]: the balance of your body, all of that, you're mindful about it.

02:04:00.280 --> 02:04:02.080
[Amit Varma]: Later, you internalize it completely

02:04:02.280 --> 02:04:05.080
[Amit Varma]: and you don't need to actually think consciously about it.

02:04:05.280 --> 02:04:07.080
[Amit Varma]: Now, in your case, the learning process seems to have been

02:04:07.280 --> 02:04:10.080
[Amit Varma]: and again, a reading habit I keep saying is the best way to become a good writer.

02:04:10.280 --> 02:04:14.080
[Amit Varma]: So a lot of it seems to have come from osmosis just by reading a lot.

02:04:14.280 --> 02:04:18.080
[Amit Varma]: You read a lot of great storytelling and then that translates into the way you write

02:04:18.280 --> 02:04:21.080
[Amit Varma]: and you've picked up a lot of good habits without even realizing it.

02:04:21.280 --> 02:04:23.080
[Amit Varma]: And that's not mindful.

02:04:23.080 --> 02:04:25.880
[Amit Varma]: And then some of it is mindful, especially when we start teaching.

02:04:26.080 --> 02:04:27.880
[Amit Varma]: You know, you start noticing that stuff mindfully

02:04:28.080 --> 02:04:30.880
[Amit Varma]: or if you're studying a writer, you like you reverse engineer what they've done

02:04:31.080 --> 02:04:32.880
[Amit Varma]: and you know, all of that.

02:04:33.080 --> 02:04:35.880
[Amit Varma]: So like I keep reminding myself, though,

02:04:36.080 --> 02:04:39.880
[Amit Varma]: I always say when it comes to reading that for me, there's no difference.

02:04:40.080 --> 02:04:42.880
[Amit Varma]: I mean, as long as you're reading, I don't care if it's mindful or otherwise,

02:04:43.080 --> 02:04:45.880
[Amit Varma]: because if what you're reading is something that captivates you,

02:04:46.080 --> 02:04:47.880
[Amit Varma]: you'll pick up things from it by osmosis.

02:04:48.080 --> 02:04:51.880
[Amit Varma]: But do you feel that it helps to be more mindful

02:04:51.880 --> 02:04:55.680
[Amit Varma]: that we should all be more mindful in terms of craft of the things that we do,

02:04:55.880 --> 02:04:58.680
[Amit Varma]: whether it is something in a cricketing technique sense,

02:04:58.880 --> 02:05:02.680
[Amit Varma]: whether it is something in a writing sense, you know, all of these things?

02:05:02.880 --> 02:05:05.680
[Guest]: You know, it's funny.

02:05:05.880 --> 02:05:07.680
[Guest]: You will try to be mine.

02:05:07.880 --> 02:05:10.680
[Guest]: My recent experience has been I will try to be mindful about,

02:05:10.880 --> 02:05:13.680
[Guest]: you know, reading or consuming any kind of content.

02:05:13.880 --> 02:05:16.680
[Guest]: And, you know, I teach a multimedia journalism course.

02:05:16.880 --> 02:05:20.680
[Guest]: So it's, you know, videos, podcasts, writing, that kind of thing.

02:05:20.680 --> 02:05:24.480
[Guest]: So I keep saying that, you know, whatever content you consume,

02:05:24.680 --> 02:05:26.480
[Guest]: you're going to pick up something from it.

02:05:26.680 --> 02:05:28.480
[Guest]: And if you should try and actively do that,

02:05:28.680 --> 02:05:30.480
[Guest]: even if it's, you know, watching your favorite Netflix show.

02:05:30.680 --> 02:05:33.480
[Guest]: And a lot of these things just come

02:05:33.680 --> 02:05:36.480
[Guest]: and express themselves in content so randomly.

02:05:36.680 --> 02:05:39.480
[Guest]: Having not made notes,

02:05:39.680 --> 02:05:42.480
[Guest]: at some point, something will strike me.

02:05:42.680 --> 02:05:45.480
[Guest]: Like recently I wrote a piece on Ashwin

02:05:45.680 --> 02:05:48.480
[Guest]: and I ended it with this line.

02:05:48.480 --> 02:05:51.280
[Guest]: When is it okay to drop the alpha?

02:05:51.480 --> 02:05:53.280
[Guest]: When the pack is stronger without him.

02:05:53.480 --> 02:05:55.280
[Guest]: Yeah, a wolf reference.

02:05:55.480 --> 02:05:58.280
[Guest]: So again, where did this line come from?

02:05:58.480 --> 02:06:00.280
[Guest]: One of my sports journalism students asked me,

02:06:00.480 --> 02:06:02.280
[Guest]: how did you come up with this line?

02:06:02.480 --> 02:06:04.280
[Guest]: Game of Thrones.

02:06:04.480 --> 02:06:08.280
[Guest]: And I was not mindfully watching Game of Thrones.

02:06:08.480 --> 02:06:10.280
[Guest]: And, you know, that line in Game of Thrones where

02:06:10.480 --> 02:06:13.280
[Guest]: the strength of the pack is the wolf and the strength of the wolf is the pack.

02:06:13.480 --> 02:06:16.280
[Guest]: That's just what somehow popped up in my mind.

02:06:16.280 --> 02:06:19.080
[Guest]: Okay, let's use a wolf reference, that kind of a thing.

02:06:19.280 --> 02:06:21.080
[Guest]: I was not mindfully watching Game of Thrones,

02:06:21.280 --> 02:06:23.080
[Guest]: but it turned up.

02:06:23.280 --> 02:06:26.080
[Guest]: I don't know how, I don't know why, I can't really explain it.

02:06:26.280 --> 02:06:29.080
[Guest]: So there have been instances where, you know,

02:06:29.280 --> 02:06:32.080
[Guest]: stuff in my notes has really helped

02:06:32.280 --> 02:06:35.080
[Guest]: improve the content that I have put out.

02:06:35.280 --> 02:06:37.080
[Guest]: And there have been instances where, you know,

02:06:37.280 --> 02:06:40.080
[Guest]: stuff just comes so randomly and that sticks with people.

02:06:40.280 --> 02:06:45.080
[Guest]: So I would probably say it's a good habit to develop that mindful consumption.

02:06:45.080 --> 02:06:48.880
[Guest]: But, I mean, who are we if we can really understand?

02:06:49.080 --> 02:06:51.880
[Guest]: We're not going to pretend to understand how our brains work.

02:06:52.080 --> 02:06:53.880
[Guest]: And just like at the subconscious level,

02:06:54.080 --> 02:06:55.880
[Guest]: there is so much weird stuff happening.

02:06:56.080 --> 02:06:59.880
[Guest]: And when it will be useful and when it will be harmful, God alone knows.

02:07:00.080 --> 02:07:01.880
[Amit Varma]: Yeah, well said. That makes a lot of sense.

02:07:02.080 --> 02:07:03.880
[Amit Varma]: Let's kind of talk about your YouTubing now,

02:07:04.080 --> 02:07:06.880
[Amit Varma]: because I was watching your video about that intimidating video

02:07:07.080 --> 02:07:09.880
[Amit Varma]: I referred to at the beginning about doing commentary twice a day and all that.

02:07:10.080 --> 02:07:11.880
[Amit Varma]: And at the beginning, there is this sequence,

02:07:12.080 --> 02:07:13.880
[Amit Varma]: this montage where you're making filter coffee.

02:07:13.880 --> 02:07:15.680
[Amit Varma]: And I straight away thought of Peter McKinnon,

02:07:15.880 --> 02:07:18.680
[Amit Varma]: the YouTuber whose coffee montages are really famous.

02:07:18.880 --> 02:07:22.680
[Amit Varma]: So tell me a little bit about what got you into try YouTubing.

02:07:22.880 --> 02:07:26.680
[Amit Varma]: Did you intend to do cricket stuff or did you intend to do vloggy stuff?

02:07:26.880 --> 02:07:29.680
[Amit Varma]: Who are the YouTubers that you kind of liked?

02:07:29.880 --> 02:07:33.680
[Amit Varma]: What were the kind of values that you picked up mindfully from people?

02:07:33.880 --> 02:07:35.680
[Amit Varma]: Like that whole coffee montage, I just looked at it

02:07:35.880 --> 02:07:37.680
[Amit Varma]: and I thought she must have watched Peter McKinnon.

02:07:37.880 --> 02:07:40.680
[Amit Varma]: So now you can confirm if that's true or not.

02:07:40.680 --> 02:07:44.480
[Amit Varma]: Take me a bit through your early part of your YouTube journey as well.

02:07:44.680 --> 02:07:46.480
[Guest]: I have watched Peter McKinnon,

02:07:46.680 --> 02:07:48.480
[Guest]: but I must say that, you know, again,

02:07:48.680 --> 02:07:51.480
[Guest]: this is the weird, unconscious, subconscious stuff that I'm talking about.

02:07:51.680 --> 02:07:54.480
[Guest]: I am 100% sure that I did not think about Peter McKinnon

02:07:54.680 --> 02:07:56.480
[Guest]: probably for a year or so,

02:07:56.680 --> 02:07:58.480
[Guest]: even while I was making that coffee montage

02:07:58.680 --> 02:08:00.480
[Guest]: before you brought up his name.

02:08:00.680 --> 02:08:03.480
[Guest]: Like I watched his videos probably a long time ago.

02:08:03.680 --> 02:08:05.480
[Guest]: But again, you know, subconsciously,

02:08:05.680 --> 02:08:08.480
[Guest]: what all we internalize, God alone knows.

02:08:08.480 --> 02:08:11.280
[Guest]: If someone can figure out the subconscious one day,

02:08:11.480 --> 02:08:14.280
[Guest]: it will be a very big achievement.

02:08:14.480 --> 02:08:17.280
[Guest]: But YouTube was a very interesting phase.

02:08:17.480 --> 02:08:20.280
[Guest]: Again, I must emphasize that this was a phase

02:08:20.480 --> 02:08:23.280
[Guest]: where I was receiving a lot of support from home.

02:08:23.480 --> 02:08:27.280
[Guest]: Again, not having a regular job.

02:08:27.480 --> 02:08:30.280
[Guest]: And I say that with air quotes.

02:08:30.480 --> 02:08:32.280
[Guest]: Having quit my railway job, you know,

02:08:32.480 --> 02:08:35.280
[Guest]: much to the consternation of my grandfather,

02:08:35.480 --> 02:08:37.280
[Guest]: who still wants me to do engineering

02:08:37.280 --> 02:08:40.080
[Guest]: and have a permanent job and a pension.

02:08:40.280 --> 02:08:42.080
[Guest]: There was a tremendous amount of support from home.

02:08:42.280 --> 02:08:44.080
[Guest]: I was back in Pune living with my parents.

02:08:44.280 --> 02:08:47.080
[Guest]: And there was this space

02:08:47.280 --> 02:08:49.080
[Guest]: to kind of, you know, figure it out yourself.

02:08:49.280 --> 02:08:51.080
[Guest]: I went to Australia for a couple of months.

02:08:51.280 --> 02:08:53.080
[Guest]: There was...

02:08:53.280 --> 02:08:56.080
[Guest]: And therefore, I was in a phase of my life

02:08:56.280 --> 02:08:57.080
[Guest]: where I had a lot of time.

02:08:57.280 --> 02:08:59.080
[Guest]: You know, I was writing from time to time

02:08:59.280 --> 02:09:01.080
[Guest]: and that kind of paid the bills.

02:09:01.280 --> 02:09:03.080
[Guest]: But it was not my job.

02:09:03.280 --> 02:09:04.080
[Guest]: I was not doing it every day.

02:09:04.280 --> 02:09:06.080
[Guest]: So I had some time in my life

02:09:06.080 --> 02:09:07.880
[Guest]: kind of figuring out what I was...

02:09:08.080 --> 02:09:09.880
[Guest]: what I would like to do.

02:09:10.080 --> 02:09:12.880
[Guest]: Briefly flirting with the idea of writing a book.

02:09:13.080 --> 02:09:14.880
[Guest]: And then I...

02:09:15.080 --> 02:09:17.880
[Guest]: This is one of my favorite stories in life

02:09:18.080 --> 02:09:20.880
[Guest]: about, you know, what can lead you where.

02:09:21.080 --> 02:09:22.880
[Guest]: Then I started playing Pokemon Go.

02:09:23.080 --> 02:09:24.880
[Guest]: Okay.

02:09:25.080 --> 02:09:26.880
[Guest]: Again, you know, 90s kid

02:09:27.080 --> 02:09:28.880
[Guest]: having grown up watching those cartoons

02:09:29.080 --> 02:09:30.880
[Guest]: and Pokemon being one of those cartoons.

02:09:31.080 --> 02:09:32.880
[Guest]: This game suddenly took over the world.

02:09:33.080 --> 02:09:34.880
[Guest]: And I was like, okay, let's try it out.

02:09:34.880 --> 02:09:37.680
[Guest]: And having no idea how to play it,

02:09:37.880 --> 02:09:39.680
[Guest]: I randomly Googled

02:09:39.880 --> 02:09:40.680
[Guest]: or maybe went on to YouTube

02:09:40.880 --> 02:09:41.680
[Guest]: and tried to learn how to play it.

02:09:41.880 --> 02:09:42.680
[Guest]: And this is the first time

02:09:42.880 --> 02:09:44.680
[Guest]: I had consciously used YouTube to learn something.

02:09:44.880 --> 02:09:46.680
[Guest]: Until that, you know, YouTube was a place

02:09:46.880 --> 02:09:48.680
[Guest]: where I watched trailers once in a while

02:09:48.880 --> 02:09:50.680
[Guest]: or YouTube was a place where

02:09:50.880 --> 02:09:52.680
[Guest]: videos I was intentionally watching

02:09:52.880 --> 02:09:53.680
[Guest]: happened to be hosted.

02:09:53.880 --> 02:09:55.680
[Guest]: I didn't go on to YouTube

02:09:55.880 --> 02:09:56.680
[Guest]: to actually watch something.

02:09:56.880 --> 02:09:58.680
[Guest]: So this is the first time I'm on YouTube

02:09:58.880 --> 02:10:01.680
[Guest]: and I'm watching this video

02:10:01.880 --> 02:10:03.680
[Guest]: by a vlogger in the US.

02:10:03.680 --> 02:10:06.480
[Guest]: His name is Nick. His channel's name is Trainer Tips.

02:10:06.680 --> 02:10:09.480
[Guest]: And he's basically making daily vlogs

02:10:09.680 --> 02:10:12.480
[Guest]: explaining his processes of playing Pokemon Go.

02:10:12.680 --> 02:10:13.480
[Guest]: He's a Pokemon Go nerd.

02:10:13.680 --> 02:10:15.480
[Guest]: And I'm like, oh, these videos are cool.

02:10:15.680 --> 02:10:17.480
[Guest]: And I started playing Pokemon Go.

02:10:17.680 --> 02:10:19.480
[Guest]: I keep watching his videos regularly.

02:10:19.680 --> 02:10:23.480
[Guest]: He has this lovely vloggy style.

02:10:23.680 --> 02:10:27.480
[Guest]: And I think, hey, maybe I should try that.

02:10:27.680 --> 02:10:30.480
[Guest]: And that's literally how the YouTube channel started.

02:10:30.680 --> 02:10:32.480
[Guest]: I made a few calls

02:10:32.480 --> 02:10:35.280
[Guest]: and happened to get some advice

02:10:35.480 --> 02:10:37.280
[Guest]: from the person who today is

02:10:37.480 --> 02:10:40.280
[Guest]: the head of production for my YouTube channel.

02:10:40.480 --> 02:10:42.280
[Guest]: And he basically told me use this camera,

02:10:42.480 --> 02:10:43.280
[Guest]: use that camera.

02:10:43.480 --> 02:10:44.280
[Guest]: This is fine. That is fine.

02:10:44.480 --> 02:10:45.280
[Guest]: Just go and do it.

02:10:45.480 --> 02:10:47.280
[Guest]: And yeah, I was kind of just imitating

02:10:47.480 --> 02:10:49.280
[Guest]: what I was seeing on YouTube,

02:10:49.480 --> 02:10:50.280
[Guest]: what I was seeing on,

02:10:50.480 --> 02:10:52.280
[Guest]: what I was seeing other people do.

02:10:52.480 --> 02:10:54.280
[Guest]: And at the time, I had just gotten a dog.

02:10:54.480 --> 02:10:56.280
[Guest]: He was about a year old.

02:10:56.480 --> 02:10:59.280
[Guest]: And therefore, I was spending a lot of time outdoors with him.

02:10:59.480 --> 02:11:00.280
[Guest]: I thought, OK, let's...

02:11:00.280 --> 02:11:03.080
[Guest]: And I'm an outdoor person. I like hiking.

02:11:03.280 --> 02:11:05.080
[Guest]: I like going on any kind of

02:11:05.280 --> 02:11:07.080
[Guest]: trip which is taking you closer to nature

02:11:07.280 --> 02:11:08.080
[Guest]: and that kind of stuff.

02:11:08.280 --> 02:11:11.080
[Guest]: Even like today, it's a big part of my life.

02:11:11.280 --> 02:11:15.080
[Guest]: But I think maybe I can make a show about cricket

02:11:15.280 --> 02:11:16.080
[Guest]: done outdoors.

02:11:16.280 --> 02:11:18.080
[Guest]: You know, someone talking about cricket,

02:11:18.280 --> 02:11:19.080
[Guest]: but doing it outdoors.

02:11:19.280 --> 02:11:21.080
[Guest]: Just randomly trying to combine

02:11:21.280 --> 02:11:23.080
[Guest]: whatever passions I have

02:11:23.280 --> 02:11:25.080
[Guest]: in the most generic way possible.

02:11:25.280 --> 02:11:27.080
[Guest]: So I started making vlogs.

02:11:27.280 --> 02:11:29.080
[Guest]: If you go back to the first three videos on my channel,

02:11:29.080 --> 02:11:32.880
[Guest]: they are vlogs where I'm exploring some place

02:11:33.080 --> 02:11:34.880
[Guest]: and talking about cricket side by side.

02:11:35.080 --> 02:11:36.880
[Guest]: And this is a time where, like I said,

02:11:37.080 --> 02:11:38.880
[Guest]: I have a lot of time in my life.

02:11:39.080 --> 02:11:42.880
[Guest]: Well, I have more time than I had time.

02:11:43.080 --> 02:11:44.880
[Guest]: And therefore, I'm on YouTube learning.

02:11:45.080 --> 02:11:46.880
[Guest]: I'm learning how to use a camera.

02:11:47.080 --> 02:11:48.880
[Guest]: I'm on YouTube learning how to shoot.

02:11:49.080 --> 02:11:50.880
[Guest]: I'm on YouTube, most of all,

02:11:51.080 --> 02:11:51.880
[Guest]: most important of all,

02:11:52.080 --> 02:11:52.880
[Guest]: learning how to edit my own videos.

02:11:53.080 --> 02:11:55.880
[Guest]: Again, I am a BSc graduate

02:11:56.080 --> 02:11:57.880
[Guest]: who played cricket for 15 years,

02:11:57.880 --> 02:11:58.880
[Guest]: worked in a government office,

02:11:59.080 --> 02:12:01.680
[Guest]: have zero idea about how all this technology works.

02:12:01.880 --> 02:12:03.680
[Guest]: And suddenly YouTube is teaching me all of this.

02:12:03.880 --> 02:12:05.680
[Guest]: I was like, oh, this is so cool.

02:12:05.880 --> 02:12:08.680
[Guest]: And that process of learning

02:12:08.880 --> 02:12:11.680
[Guest]: and implementing what I've learned,

02:12:11.880 --> 02:12:13.680
[Guest]: it gives you a little bit of a high.

02:12:13.880 --> 02:12:15.680
[Guest]: It gives you a little bit of a sense of satisfaction.

02:12:15.880 --> 02:12:18.680
[Guest]: This is that, you know, A, it's so new.

02:12:18.880 --> 02:12:21.680
[Guest]: Maybe everyone nowadays finds this very normal,

02:12:21.880 --> 02:12:23.680
[Guest]: you know, having a YouTube channel and doing all this.

02:12:23.680 --> 02:12:28.480
[Guest]: 2016, I remember going to the YouTube office and the head of YouTube,

02:12:28.680 --> 02:12:30.480
[Guest]: India or head of YouTube sports,

02:12:30.680 --> 02:12:31.480
[Guest]: I think head of YouTube India.

02:12:31.680 --> 02:12:33.480
[Guest]: He's like, I remember in 2016-17,

02:12:33.680 --> 02:12:35.480
[Guest]: you were the only channel who was doing this.

02:12:35.680 --> 02:12:37.480
[Guest]: And it happened to be so.

02:12:37.680 --> 02:12:39.480
[Guest]: I was, you know, happened to be one of the first people

02:12:39.680 --> 02:12:41.480
[Guest]: who discovered that this process of learning

02:12:41.680 --> 02:12:43.480
[Guest]: and this process of creating,

02:12:43.680 --> 02:12:45.480
[Guest]: using what you've learned on YouTube is fun.

02:12:45.680 --> 02:12:47.480
[Guest]: And so therefore, I was just doing it for fun.

02:12:47.680 --> 02:12:49.480
[Guest]: And the fourth video I made,

02:12:49.680 --> 02:12:52.480
[Guest]: I thought, let's OK, let's mix it up

02:12:52.480 --> 02:12:55.280
[Guest]: and let's make a video on how to choose a bat.

02:12:55.480 --> 02:12:58.280
[Guest]: So that was the first how to video I made.

02:12:58.480 --> 02:13:00.280
[Guest]: And I made that video.

02:13:00.480 --> 02:13:02.280
[Guest]: It's still in a vlog style

02:13:02.480 --> 02:13:04.280
[Guest]: because that's what I liked to do.

02:13:04.480 --> 02:13:06.280
[Guest]: And I still like it more than

02:13:06.480 --> 02:13:08.280
[Guest]: hardcore tutorials.

02:13:08.480 --> 02:13:11.280
[Guest]: But I made that video and it kind of exploded.

02:13:11.480 --> 02:13:14.280
[Guest]: And suddenly my channel has 4000 subscribers.

02:13:14.480 --> 02:13:16.280
[Guest]: I'm like, oh, there's something here.

02:13:16.480 --> 02:13:18.280
[Guest]: So let me think about it.

02:13:18.480 --> 02:13:20.280
[Guest]: Let me try and do it seriously.

02:13:20.280 --> 02:13:23.080
[Guest]: And that's kind of how YouTube started.

02:13:23.280 --> 02:13:25.080
[Amit Varma]: And you have, I think, more than 300,000 now

02:13:25.280 --> 02:13:26.080
[Amit Varma]: or something like that.

02:13:26.280 --> 02:13:28.080
[Guest]: Some 2,80,000 right now.

02:13:28.280 --> 02:13:30.080
[Amit Varma]: 2,80,000. OK.

02:13:30.280 --> 02:13:32.080
[Amit Varma]: So like one of the things I noted,

02:13:32.280 --> 02:13:34.080
[Amit Varma]: which I alluded to earlier,

02:13:34.280 --> 02:13:37.080
[Amit Varma]: but one of the things I noted about your YouTube

02:13:37.280 --> 02:13:39.080
[Amit Varma]: as it is now from the recent videos that I watched

02:13:39.280 --> 02:13:41.080
[Amit Varma]: is a lack of self-consciousness.

02:13:41.280 --> 02:13:43.080
[Amit Varma]: Is that it's just, you know,

02:13:43.280 --> 02:13:44.080
[Amit Varma]: you're not overthinking it.

02:13:44.280 --> 02:13:46.080
[Amit Varma]: You're not trying to be too stylized

02:13:46.280 --> 02:13:48.080
[Amit Varma]: despite the filter coffee montage.

02:13:48.080 --> 02:13:50.880
[Amit Varma]: It's almost like what you see is what you get.

02:13:51.080 --> 02:13:52.880
[Amit Varma]: And, you know, one of the sort of the things

02:13:53.080 --> 02:13:55.880
[Amit Varma]: that I say that creators should pay more attention to

02:13:56.080 --> 02:13:56.880
[Amit Varma]: and should cultivate.

02:13:57.080 --> 02:13:57.880
[Amit Varma]: And that's an important quality.

02:13:58.080 --> 02:13:59.880
[Amit Varma]: It's just authenticity in terms of

02:14:00.080 --> 02:14:01.880
[Amit Varma]: being authentic to who you are.

02:14:02.080 --> 02:14:03.880
[Amit Varma]: All the creators I enjoy listening to in podcasts

02:14:04.080 --> 02:14:05.880
[Amit Varma]: or watching on YouTube

02:14:06.080 --> 02:14:07.880
[Amit Varma]: are just authentic to who they are.

02:14:08.080 --> 02:14:10.880
[Amit Varma]: You know, whatever the subject might be of the podcast

02:14:11.080 --> 02:14:12.880
[Amit Varma]: or their particular video or whatever,

02:14:13.080 --> 02:14:13.880
[Amit Varma]: I'm really watching it for them.

02:14:14.080 --> 02:14:15.880
[Amit Varma]: I've kind of gotten a comfort level with them.

02:14:15.880 --> 02:14:18.680
[Amit Varma]: And therefore, that's why I'm there.

02:14:18.880 --> 02:14:19.680
[Amit Varma]: That's why I'm hooked.

02:14:19.880 --> 02:14:20.680
[Amit Varma]: That's why I'm kind of going there.

02:14:20.880 --> 02:14:22.680
[Amit Varma]: So, you know, again, is this something

02:14:22.880 --> 02:14:24.680
[Amit Varma]: that was there from the start

02:14:24.880 --> 02:14:27.680
[Amit Varma]: or is it something that you kind of evolved to?

02:14:27.880 --> 02:14:28.680
[Amit Varma]: Like, did you, was there a time

02:14:28.880 --> 02:14:29.680
[Amit Varma]: where you were overthinking it?

02:14:29.880 --> 02:14:32.680
[Amit Varma]: Was there a time where, you know,

02:14:32.880 --> 02:14:35.680
[Amit Varma]: you thought more stylistic takes were important

02:14:35.880 --> 02:14:38.680
[Amit Varma]: or you just figured out that this is the easiest way

02:14:38.880 --> 02:14:40.680
[Amit Varma]: to do it and not to overthink it

02:14:40.880 --> 02:14:42.680
[Guest]: and so on and so forth?

02:14:42.680 --> 02:14:45.480
[Guest]: I don't think that's completely what it is.

02:14:45.680 --> 02:14:46.480
[Guest]: Like, for example,

02:14:46.680 --> 02:14:47.480
[Guest]: that video that you mentioned,

02:14:47.680 --> 02:14:48.480
[Guest]: the day in the life,

02:14:48.680 --> 02:14:51.480
[Guest]: you know, it starts with me really bleary eyed.

02:14:51.680 --> 02:14:53.480
[Amit Varma]: Exactly, you're not trying too hard

02:14:53.680 --> 02:14:54.480
[Amit Varma]: to make yourself look good,

02:14:54.680 --> 02:14:56.480
[Amit Varma]: which is great, which is...

02:14:56.680 --> 02:14:58.480
[Guest]: Yeah, and in that video,

02:14:58.680 --> 02:14:59.480
[Guest]: I was consciously doing that.

02:14:59.680 --> 02:15:01.480
[Guest]: Like, literally, I decided first thing in the morning,

02:15:01.680 --> 02:15:02.480
[Guest]: I'm going to film.

02:15:02.680 --> 02:15:03.480
[Guest]: But while watching it back,

02:15:03.680 --> 02:15:05.480
[Guest]: I was like, oh God, that looks so bad.

02:15:05.680 --> 02:15:08.480
[Amit Varma]: No, I disagree.

02:15:08.480 --> 02:15:12.280
[Guest]: And, you know, later on the video,

02:15:12.480 --> 02:15:13.280
[Guest]: looking at it and thinking,

02:15:13.480 --> 02:15:14.280
[Guest]: oh, there's like a weird,

02:15:14.480 --> 02:15:16.280
[Guest]: curly hair sticking out here

02:15:16.480 --> 02:15:18.280
[Guest]: and this should have been better

02:15:18.480 --> 02:15:19.280
[Guest]: and that should have been better.

02:15:19.480 --> 02:15:20.280
[Guest]: And when I'm filming,

02:15:20.480 --> 02:15:23.280
[Guest]: I do try and present.

02:15:23.480 --> 02:15:25.280
[Guest]: There is absolutely,

02:15:25.480 --> 02:15:27.280
[Guest]: I mean, it's kind of become part of my job,

02:15:27.480 --> 02:15:30.280
[Guest]: presenting, but at the same time,

02:15:30.480 --> 02:15:33.280
[Guest]: not presenting too much.

02:15:33.480 --> 02:15:37.280
[Guest]: If you meet me outside of YouTube,

02:15:37.280 --> 02:15:39.080
[Guest]: I'm definitely going to talk differently.

02:15:39.280 --> 02:15:40.080
[Guest]: I don't have...

02:15:40.280 --> 02:15:41.080
[Guest]: I have a script,

02:15:41.280 --> 02:15:42.080
[Guest]: for example, on YouTube.

02:15:42.280 --> 02:15:43.080
[Guest]: Usually, I'll have a fair idea

02:15:43.280 --> 02:15:45.080
[Guest]: of what I want to say.

02:15:45.280 --> 02:15:46.080
[Guest]: I will do takes.

02:15:46.280 --> 02:15:48.080
[Guest]: I'm not, you know,

02:15:48.280 --> 02:15:50.080
[Guest]: this absolute authenticity person.

02:15:50.280 --> 02:15:51.080
[Guest]: But at the same time,

02:15:51.280 --> 02:15:52.080
[Guest]: as a person,

02:15:52.280 --> 02:15:56.080
[Guest]: I'm not a person who worries a lot

02:15:56.280 --> 02:15:57.080
[Guest]: about how I look.

02:15:57.280 --> 02:15:59.080
[Guest]: I'm not a person who,

02:15:59.280 --> 02:16:00.080
[Guest]: you know,

02:16:00.280 --> 02:16:02.080
[Guest]: I've never been into makeup.

02:16:02.280 --> 02:16:04.080
[Guest]: In fact, that's one of my worst,

02:16:04.280 --> 02:16:06.080
[Guest]: that's one of the things I like the least

02:16:06.080 --> 02:16:08.880
[Guest]: about having to sometimes work in TV

02:16:09.080 --> 02:16:09.880
[Guest]: or in a studio.

02:16:10.080 --> 02:16:12.880
[Guest]: The just uncomfortable amount of makeup

02:16:13.080 --> 02:16:14.880
[Guest]: that they put on us.

02:16:15.080 --> 02:16:17.880
[Guest]: I've never been someone who has,

02:16:18.080 --> 02:16:19.880
[Guest]: you know, consciously gone out of the way

02:16:20.080 --> 02:16:21.880
[Guest]: to dress in a certain way.

02:16:22.080 --> 02:16:24.880
[Guest]: Usually, I'll just be most comfortable

02:16:25.080 --> 02:16:25.880
[Guest]: in what I'm most comfortable.

02:16:26.080 --> 02:16:28.880
[Guest]: And I think that comes across.

02:16:29.080 --> 02:16:30.880
[Guest]: That comes across as,

02:16:31.080 --> 02:16:32.880
[Guest]: you know, even stylistically of

02:16:32.880 --> 02:16:36.680
[Guest]: I'm okay with a first thing in the morning shot

02:16:36.880 --> 02:16:38.680
[Guest]: because that's what it's supposed to be.

02:16:38.880 --> 02:16:39.680
[Guest]: It's a first thing in the morning shot.

02:16:39.880 --> 02:16:41.680
[Guest]: But if it's supposed to be a shot

02:16:41.880 --> 02:16:44.680
[Guest]: where I'm really trying to convey

02:16:44.880 --> 02:16:46.680
[Guest]: a crisp, organized look,

02:16:46.880 --> 02:16:48.680
[Guest]: which is still me,

02:16:48.880 --> 02:16:49.680
[Guest]: I will do that.

02:16:49.880 --> 02:16:50.680
[Guest]: I will put in the effort to

02:16:50.880 --> 02:16:53.680
[Guest]: make sure that I am so presentable.

02:16:53.880 --> 02:16:55.680
[Guest]: And there is a certain amount of,

02:16:55.880 --> 02:16:57.680
[Guest]: I mean, off camera,

02:16:57.880 --> 02:16:58.680
[Guest]: I'm slightly different,

02:16:58.880 --> 02:17:00.680
[Guest]: but only slightly.

02:17:00.680 --> 02:17:03.480
[Guest]: And that's probably the best way to describe it.

02:17:03.680 --> 02:17:04.480
[Amit Varma]: Yeah, I know.

02:17:04.680 --> 02:17:05.480
[Amit Varma]: I get what you're saying that,

02:17:05.680 --> 02:17:06.480
[Amit Varma]: you know, like,

02:17:06.680 --> 02:17:08.480
[Amit Varma]: even the intros to my podcast,

02:17:08.680 --> 02:17:09.480
[Amit Varma]: like in this conversation,

02:17:09.680 --> 02:17:10.480
[Amit Varma]: I'm just being me.

02:17:10.680 --> 02:17:11.480
[Amit Varma]: But in the intro to my podcast,

02:17:11.680 --> 02:17:12.480
[Amit Varma]: I am kind of presenting,

02:17:12.680 --> 02:17:14.480
[Amit Varma]: but it's also kind of me.

02:17:14.680 --> 02:17:15.480
[Amit Varma]: It's not contrived.

02:17:15.680 --> 02:17:17.480
[Amit Varma]: That's a similar thing.

02:17:17.680 --> 02:17:18.480
[Amit Varma]: So I get what you mean

02:17:18.680 --> 02:17:19.480
[Amit Varma]: when you say you're presenting

02:17:19.680 --> 02:17:20.480
[Amit Varma]: and you've got a script and all that.

02:17:20.680 --> 02:17:21.480
[Amit Varma]: Yeah, I get that.

02:17:21.680 --> 02:17:22.480
[Amit Varma]: But at the same time,

02:17:22.680 --> 02:17:23.480
[Amit Varma]: it doesn't feel contrived.

02:17:23.680 --> 02:17:26.480
[Guest]: I'm not trying to make it not feel contrived.

02:17:26.680 --> 02:17:27.480
[Amit Varma]: Yeah.

02:17:27.680 --> 02:17:28.480
[Guest]: While at the same time,

02:17:28.480 --> 02:17:31.280
[Guest]: I'm not trying to make it, you know,

02:17:31.480 --> 02:17:32.280
[Guest]: unless it's a vlog like that,

02:17:32.480 --> 02:17:33.280
[Guest]: I'm not trying to make it

02:17:33.480 --> 02:17:35.280
[Guest]: look completely casual either.

02:17:35.480 --> 02:17:36.280
[Amit Varma]: Yeah.

02:17:36.480 --> 02:17:38.280
[Guest]: I mean, I will pay more attention to the lighting

02:17:38.480 --> 02:17:40.280
[Guest]: than I will to hairstyle.

02:17:40.480 --> 02:17:41.280
[Guest]: That's me.

02:17:41.480 --> 02:17:43.280
[Amit Varma]: Yeah, that's kind of remarkable

02:17:43.480 --> 02:17:45.280
[Amit Varma]: because I think that kind of

02:17:45.480 --> 02:17:47.280
[Amit Varma]: lack of self-consciousness is just great.

02:17:47.480 --> 02:17:48.280
[Amit Varma]: Like, you know,

02:17:48.480 --> 02:17:51.280
[Amit Varma]: I'm also thinking of starting something on YouTube

02:17:51.480 --> 02:17:53.280
[Amit Varma]: and that self-consciousness about

02:17:53.480 --> 02:17:55.280
[Amit Varma]: just the physical aspect of it is,

02:17:55.480 --> 02:17:57.280
[Amit Varma]: you know, kind of the biggest

02:17:57.280 --> 02:17:59.080
[Amit Varma]: stumbling block, though I know that

02:17:59.280 --> 02:18:00.080
[Amit Varma]: once I start and I get past it,

02:18:00.280 --> 02:18:01.080
[Amit Varma]: it's kind of fine.

02:18:01.280 --> 02:18:03.080
[Amit Varma]: But, you know, audio is easy that way.

02:18:03.280 --> 02:18:05.080
[Amit Varma]: You don't really have to worry.

02:18:05.280 --> 02:18:06.080
[Guest]: No, there I totally agree,

02:18:06.280 --> 02:18:07.080
[Guest]: which is why, I mean,

02:18:07.280 --> 02:18:09.080
[Guest]: you know, out of the commentary work that I do,

02:18:09.280 --> 02:18:12.080
[Guest]: doing radio commentary is my favorite

02:18:12.280 --> 02:18:14.080
[Guest]: because there it's not about

02:18:14.280 --> 02:18:15.080
[Guest]: what you look like.

02:18:15.280 --> 02:18:17.080
[Guest]: It's about what you know and how you say it.

02:18:17.280 --> 02:18:21.080
[Guest]: And that is the probably

02:18:21.280 --> 02:18:23.080
[Guest]: most natural form of commentary

02:18:23.280 --> 02:18:25.080
[Guest]: that I've experienced.

02:18:25.080 --> 02:18:27.880
[Guest]: And that is something that I really enjoy doing

02:18:28.080 --> 02:18:28.880
[Guest]: purely for the reason that, you know,

02:18:29.080 --> 02:18:30.880
[Guest]: you don't have to present visually.

02:18:31.080 --> 02:18:32.880
[Guest]: You just need to present almost

02:18:33.080 --> 02:18:34.880
[Guest]: intellectually and vocally.

02:18:35.080 --> 02:18:36.880
[Amit Varma]: So let's talk about commentary.

02:18:37.080 --> 02:18:37.880
[Amit Varma]: Like, you know,

02:18:38.080 --> 02:18:39.880
[Amit Varma]: there are very different views

02:18:40.080 --> 02:18:41.880
[Amit Varma]: of what good commentary is.

02:18:42.080 --> 02:18:43.880
[Amit Varma]: Before satellite television kind of took over India,

02:18:44.080 --> 02:18:45.880
[Amit Varma]: if you go back to the Ritchie Beno school of thinking,

02:18:46.080 --> 02:18:47.880
[Amit Varma]: the Ritchie Beno school of thinking

02:18:48.080 --> 02:18:49.880
[Amit Varma]: really is that the viewer can see

02:18:50.080 --> 02:18:50.880
[Amit Varma]: what is happening on the screen.

02:18:51.080 --> 02:18:51.880
[Amit Varma]: You don't need to describe it.

02:18:52.080 --> 02:18:53.880
[Amit Varma]: If you have something to say with that

02:18:53.880 --> 02:18:55.680
[Amit Varma]: adds to that, say it.

02:18:55.880 --> 02:18:57.680
[Amit Varma]: Otherwise, keep quiet.

02:18:57.880 --> 02:18:58.680
[Amit Varma]: Whereas, you know,

02:18:58.880 --> 02:19:00.680
[Amit Varma]: the brief on Indian satellite television

02:19:00.880 --> 02:19:03.680
[Amit Varma]: for the early group of commentators in the 90s

02:19:03.880 --> 02:19:05.680
[Amit Varma]: was simply that don't let there be a quiet moment.

02:19:05.880 --> 02:19:07.680
[Amit Varma]: So you kind of had to talk.

02:19:07.880 --> 02:19:09.680
[Amit Varma]: You had to sort of fill all the space

02:19:09.880 --> 02:19:11.680
[Amit Varma]: with the description and that

02:19:11.880 --> 02:19:12.680
[Amit Varma]: there was a danger there

02:19:12.880 --> 02:19:14.680
[Amit Varma]: that then you just get banal

02:19:14.880 --> 02:19:17.680
[Amit Varma]: and, you know, all of those things kind of happen.

02:19:17.880 --> 02:19:20.680
[Amit Varma]: So when you started doing commentary,

02:19:20.880 --> 02:19:22.680
[Amit Varma]: what was the kind of brief you gave to yourself?

02:19:22.680 --> 02:19:25.480
[Amit Varma]: Like, how does one define good commentary?

02:19:25.680 --> 02:19:27.480
[Amit Varma]: And obviously, it's different on TV and radio

02:19:27.680 --> 02:19:29.480
[Amit Varma]: because radio, the person isn't actually seeing the action.

02:19:29.680 --> 02:19:31.480
[Amit Varma]: So you got to get into that as well.

02:19:31.680 --> 02:19:34.480
[Amit Varma]: But what was your notion of commentary going in?

02:19:34.680 --> 02:19:35.480
[Amit Varma]: How did it evolve?

02:19:35.680 --> 02:19:37.480
[Amit Varma]: How did your style as a commentator evolve?

02:19:37.680 --> 02:19:39.480
[Amit Varma]: And what did you find difficult?

02:19:39.680 --> 02:19:41.480
[Amit Varma]: And what did you not find difficult, so to say?

02:19:41.680 --> 02:19:44.480
[Guest]: So my first experience with commentary

02:19:44.680 --> 02:19:46.480
[Guest]: was probably Australia,

02:19:46.680 --> 02:19:48.480
[Guest]: where I went and, you know,

02:19:48.680 --> 02:19:51.480
[Guest]: word got around that there's someone from India here.

02:19:51.480 --> 02:19:53.280
[Guest]: And since there was subjects of interest

02:19:53.480 --> 02:19:55.280
[Guest]: in terms of two Indian players,

02:19:55.480 --> 02:19:57.280
[Guest]: ABC Radio wanted to get some perspective,

02:19:57.480 --> 02:19:58.280
[Guest]: get the Indian perspective.

02:19:58.480 --> 02:20:01.280
[Guest]: And that was the first time I put on a mic

02:20:01.480 --> 02:20:02.280
[Guest]: and quite nervous.

02:20:02.480 --> 02:20:05.280
[Guest]: Luckily, I had the role there of an expert.

02:20:05.480 --> 02:20:07.280
[Guest]: So, you know, you would usually

02:20:07.480 --> 02:20:09.280
[Guest]: describe commentators in two roles.

02:20:09.480 --> 02:20:11.280
[Guest]: One is a caller and one is an expert,

02:20:11.480 --> 02:20:13.280
[Guest]: where the caller is having to,

02:20:13.480 --> 02:20:15.280
[Guest]: especially on radio, describe what happened

02:20:15.480 --> 02:20:17.280
[Guest]: and the expert will have to

02:20:17.480 --> 02:20:19.280
[Guest]: describe why it happened.

02:20:19.280 --> 02:20:22.080
[Guest]: So the first few opportunities that I got were opportunities

02:20:22.280 --> 02:20:24.080
[Guest]: which were usually, you know, in the break commentary

02:20:24.280 --> 02:20:25.080
[Guest]: where I could just talk about

02:20:25.280 --> 02:20:27.080
[Guest]: my experience with women's cricket.

02:20:27.280 --> 02:20:30.080
[Guest]: And that felt fairly natural.

02:20:30.280 --> 02:20:32.080
[Guest]: It felt fairly, you know, OK.

02:20:32.280 --> 02:20:34.080
[Guest]: I know my stuff.

02:20:34.280 --> 02:20:36.080
[Guest]: So therefore, I can put it across.

02:20:36.280 --> 02:20:39.080
[Guest]: Like I said, I mean, communication in English

02:20:39.280 --> 02:20:41.080
[Guest]: had always been a strength.

02:20:41.280 --> 02:20:44.080
[Guest]: So this was just about overcoming

02:20:44.280 --> 02:20:45.080
[Guest]: those initial butterflies of,

02:20:45.280 --> 02:20:47.080
[Guest]: oh my God, your life

02:20:47.280 --> 02:20:48.080
[Guest]: and getting started.

02:20:48.080 --> 02:20:50.880
[Guest]: And once I got started, I used to usually get into the flow.

02:20:51.080 --> 02:20:52.880
[Guest]: So that was how radio went.

02:20:53.080 --> 02:20:55.880
[Guest]: When I went to TV for the first time,

02:20:56.080 --> 02:20:57.880
[Guest]: this was, I got an opportunity to commentate

02:20:58.080 --> 02:20:58.880
[Guest]: on a challenger trophy,

02:20:59.080 --> 02:21:00.880
[Guest]: a women's challenger trophy.

02:21:01.080 --> 02:21:02.880
[Guest]: First time commentating with the BCCI,

02:21:03.080 --> 02:21:04.880
[Guest]: first time commentating

02:21:05.080 --> 02:21:06.880
[Guest]: on something that is going up on TV

02:21:07.080 --> 02:21:08.880
[Guest]: on a major channel like Star Sports.

02:21:09.080 --> 02:21:11.880
[Guest]: There, the brief to myself was

02:21:12.080 --> 02:21:12.880
[Guest]: play your role.

02:21:13.080 --> 02:21:15.880
[Guest]: Again, usually I was only slotted as the expert

02:21:15.880 --> 02:21:17.680
[Guest]: because inexperienced as a caller.

02:21:17.880 --> 02:21:20.680
[Guest]: In India, the culture is kind of different in TV commentary.

02:21:20.880 --> 02:21:21.680
[Guest]: The roles mix.

02:21:21.880 --> 02:21:24.680
[Guest]: A former cricketer can be both expert and caller

02:21:24.880 --> 02:21:27.680
[Guest]: depending on your position in the roster.

02:21:27.880 --> 02:21:30.680
[Guest]: Usually, my role has been of the expert

02:21:30.880 --> 02:21:34.680
[Guest]: being trying to add some layer of insight.

02:21:34.880 --> 02:21:36.680
[Guest]: And that was probably one brief I had to myself

02:21:36.880 --> 02:21:38.680
[Guest]: that, you know, if this is happening,

02:21:38.880 --> 02:21:40.680
[Guest]: what is the background story?

02:21:40.880 --> 02:21:44.680
[Guest]: And that's one area I worked really hard.

02:21:44.680 --> 02:21:46.480
[Guest]: The whole journalistic training of, you know,

02:21:46.680 --> 02:21:48.480
[Guest]: interviews, research,

02:21:48.680 --> 02:21:51.480
[Guest]: really helped in that sense that

02:21:51.680 --> 02:21:54.480
[Guest]: I remember that challenger trophy, in fact.

02:21:54.680 --> 02:21:56.480
[Guest]: I got there a day before.

02:21:56.680 --> 02:21:58.480
[Guest]: I tried to watch practice.

02:21:58.680 --> 02:22:00.480
[Guest]: You know, I arranged to stay with a friend.

02:22:00.680 --> 02:22:03.480
[Guest]: I hadn't actually got official accommodation that day.

02:22:03.680 --> 02:22:05.480
[Guest]: But I arranged to stay with a friend,

02:22:05.680 --> 02:22:06.480
[Guest]: watch practice.

02:22:06.680 --> 02:22:09.480
[Guest]: The next night, once I checked into my official accommodation

02:22:09.680 --> 02:22:11.480
[Guest]: which is the same hotel the players were staying,

02:22:11.680 --> 02:22:13.480
[Guest]: I went around room to room

02:22:13.480 --> 02:22:16.280
[Guest]: and sat the players down and had a chat with them.

02:22:16.480 --> 02:22:17.280
[Guest]: What's your back story?

02:22:17.480 --> 02:22:18.280
[Guest]: Where do you come from?

02:22:18.480 --> 02:22:20.280
[Guest]: And especially the younger players

02:22:20.480 --> 02:22:22.280
[Guest]: because I had been retired a couple of years.

02:22:22.480 --> 02:22:24.280
[Guest]: There were players who I had not played with and against.

02:22:24.480 --> 02:22:25.280
[Guest]: I didn't know their stories.

02:22:25.480 --> 02:22:27.280
[Guest]: I had to make sure I knew their stories

02:22:27.480 --> 02:22:30.280
[Guest]: because, like, I am the voice of these people.

02:22:30.480 --> 02:22:32.280
[Guest]: I am the one who is responsible with telling their stories.

02:22:32.480 --> 02:22:34.280
[Guest]: So I had to make sure I knew those stories.

02:22:34.480 --> 02:22:36.280
[Guest]: So I went room to room chatting.

02:22:36.480 --> 02:22:38.280
[Guest]: Like, Didi, up!

02:22:38.480 --> 02:22:41.280
[Guest]: That kind of a, like, completely unscheduled, unannounced,

02:22:41.280 --> 02:22:45.080
[Guest]: Hi, I am just going to take 15 minutes of your time and ask you about your life.

02:22:45.280 --> 02:22:47.080
[Guest]: Kind of conversations.

02:22:47.280 --> 02:22:48.080
[Unknown]: And that helped.

02:22:48.280 --> 02:22:51.080
[Guest]: I mean, if you are caught on a moment

02:22:51.280 --> 02:22:54.080
[Guest]: where, you know, the caller has thrown to you,

02:22:54.280 --> 02:22:55.080
[Guest]: Snehal, tell us about this person.

02:22:55.280 --> 02:23:00.080
[Guest]: And you don't know that comes across on TV

02:23:00.280 --> 02:23:01.080
[Guest]: or on commentary as bad commentary.

02:23:01.280 --> 02:23:03.080
[Guest]: It comes across that you are faking it.

02:23:03.280 --> 02:23:06.080
[Guest]: And if you actually have done the research,

02:23:06.280 --> 02:23:07.080
[Guest]: then you can tell the stories.

02:23:07.280 --> 02:23:10.080
[Guest]: And that might have been the brief I gave to myself.

02:23:10.080 --> 02:23:12.880
[Guest]: Is that, you know, A, it's your responsibility to tell these stories.

02:23:13.080 --> 02:23:14.880
[Guest]: B, it's your responsibility to grow the game.

02:23:15.080 --> 02:23:17.880
[Guest]: And that is kind of one of the things

02:23:18.080 --> 02:23:21.880
[Guest]: that has driven a lot of my later career.

02:23:22.080 --> 02:23:25.880
[Guest]: I mean, even one of the reasons I got into writing on women's cricket

02:23:26.080 --> 02:23:28.880
[Guest]: and I did most of my early writing on women's cricket

02:23:29.080 --> 02:23:31.880
[Guest]: was that no one was writing about women's cricket.

02:23:32.080 --> 02:23:32.880
[Guest]: And I knew I could.

02:23:33.080 --> 02:23:34.880
[Guest]: And I knew I could make an impact.

02:23:35.080 --> 02:23:37.880
[Guest]: So the same kind of awareness while going into commentary

02:23:37.880 --> 02:23:41.680
[Guest]: where if you do this well, it will help grow the game

02:23:41.880 --> 02:23:42.680
[Guest]: in whatever small way.

02:23:42.880 --> 02:23:43.680
[Guest]: They are the story.

02:23:43.880 --> 02:23:46.680
[Guest]: They are the ones who are going to do it primarily.

02:23:46.880 --> 02:23:48.680
[Guest]: I am just a storyteller.

02:23:48.880 --> 02:23:50.680
[Guest]: That was kind of the brief I gave myself.

02:23:50.880 --> 02:23:53.680
[Guest]: But I always had an awareness that, you know,

02:23:53.880 --> 02:23:56.680
[Guest]: unless both those aspects are in sync,

02:23:56.880 --> 02:23:59.680
[Guest]: the value of what is happening on the field

02:23:59.880 --> 02:24:01.680
[Guest]: won't go across to the viewer or the listener.

02:24:01.880 --> 02:24:05.680
[Amit Varma]: One kind of strand, one sense that I got through your writings

02:24:05.680 --> 02:24:08.480
[Amit Varma]: and your videos and stuff was that

02:24:08.680 --> 02:24:12.480
[Amit Varma]: much of the stuff that you did after actually retiring as a player

02:24:12.680 --> 02:24:16.480
[Amit Varma]: was driven by your passion for women's cricket in India.

02:24:16.680 --> 02:24:18.480
[Amit Varma]: Like you talk about how, you know, you loved coaching

02:24:18.680 --> 02:24:20.480
[Amit Varma]: because, you know, you didn't get that coaching.

02:24:20.680 --> 02:24:23.480
[Amit Varma]: And now all these girls have access to that coaching.

02:24:23.680 --> 02:24:26.480
[Amit Varma]: Similarly, you know, writing about the women's game,

02:24:26.680 --> 02:24:28.480
[Amit Varma]: nobody else is doing it, so you're doing it.

02:24:28.680 --> 02:24:30.480
[Amit Varma]: Not just coaching cricket, also coaching sports journalism.

02:24:30.680 --> 02:24:34.480
[Amit Varma]: You're also now not just writing about women's cricket,

02:24:34.480 --> 02:24:36.280
[Amit Varma]: but just writing about cricket, you know,

02:24:36.480 --> 02:24:38.280
[Amit Varma]: writing about cricket really, really well.

02:24:38.480 --> 02:24:41.280
[Amit Varma]: So is that passion still sort of the single driving force

02:24:41.480 --> 02:24:43.280
[Amit Varma]: that gets you into all of this?

02:24:43.480 --> 02:24:45.280
[Amit Varma]: Or do you see yourself as a creator

02:24:45.480 --> 02:24:48.280
[Amit Varma]: outside of someone who's come as a former player herself?

02:24:48.480 --> 02:24:50.280
[Amit Varma]: Do you also see yourself as a creator?

02:24:50.480 --> 02:24:54.280
[Amit Varma]: Like I noticed that you also got another sideways YouTube channel

02:24:54.480 --> 02:24:55.280
[Amit Varma]: which is not about cricket coaching,

02:24:55.480 --> 02:24:56.280
[Amit Varma]: which is just about vlogging.

02:24:56.480 --> 02:24:59.280
[Amit Varma]: And you did a recent vlog about the trek you took and stuff.

02:24:59.480 --> 02:25:02.280
[Amit Varma]: So, like, was it always the case that you thought that,

02:25:02.280 --> 02:25:05.080
[Amit Varma]: oh, I'm a creator and I'll do these cricket things?

02:25:05.280 --> 02:25:07.080
[Amit Varma]: Or were you driven into these things

02:25:07.280 --> 02:25:08.080
[Amit Varma]: because of your passion for cricket?

02:25:08.280 --> 02:25:11.080
[Amit Varma]: And then you kind of began to redefine and expand.

02:25:11.280 --> 02:25:13.080
[Amit Varma]: So what's been your thought process

02:25:13.280 --> 02:25:16.080
[Amit Varma]: and your sort of the way that you look at yourself?

02:25:16.280 --> 02:25:19.080
[Guest]: I definitely think of myself as a creator,

02:25:19.280 --> 02:25:21.080
[Guest]: but this creator would not exist

02:25:21.280 --> 02:25:24.080
[Guest]: if that passion for women's cricket was not there.

02:25:24.280 --> 02:25:29.080
[Guest]: I mean, that was the material that needed an outlet.

02:25:29.280 --> 02:25:31.080
[Guest]: And that outlet happened to be, you know,

02:25:31.080 --> 02:25:33.880
[Guest]: starting with writing and mostly the women's cricket stuff

02:25:34.080 --> 02:25:35.880
[Guest]: has been conveyed through my writing.

02:25:36.080 --> 02:25:39.880
[Guest]: YouTube has mostly been stuff where I enjoy this process of,

02:25:40.080 --> 02:25:41.880
[Guest]: like I said, learning and then applying.

02:25:42.080 --> 02:25:44.880
[Guest]: Similarly, learning and then sharing what you've learned

02:25:45.080 --> 02:25:48.880
[Guest]: is also something that gives you a little bit of a kick

02:25:49.080 --> 02:25:50.880
[Guest]: or gives me a little bit of a kick.

02:25:51.080 --> 02:25:55.880
[Guest]: And I enjoy that process independent of women's cricket

02:25:56.080 --> 02:25:58.880
[Guest]: or independent of my passion for cricket in general.

02:25:58.880 --> 02:26:02.680
[Guest]: I mean, my passion for cricket is not completely,

02:26:02.880 --> 02:26:04.680
[Guest]: how to say, indestructible.

02:26:04.880 --> 02:26:07.680
[Guest]: Like there will be phases and there was a phase

02:26:07.880 --> 02:26:10.680
[Guest]: just after the IPL after having done commentary almost every day

02:26:10.880 --> 02:26:13.680
[Guest]: where I didn't want to watch cricket for one week.

02:26:13.880 --> 02:26:15.680
[Guest]: But there I still might feel like, you know,

02:26:15.880 --> 02:26:18.680
[Guest]: I might be able to make a video or I might be able to do other stuff.

02:26:18.880 --> 02:26:24.680
[Guest]: So the passion for the subject definitely existed first

02:26:24.680 --> 02:26:29.480
[Guest]: and then the outlet for it has probably defined me as a creator.

02:26:29.680 --> 02:26:34.480
[Guest]: But if you ask me what I will want to and be passionate about creating,

02:26:34.680 --> 02:26:37.480
[Guest]: it will always be something related to growing the game,

02:26:37.680 --> 02:26:39.480
[Guest]: growing the women's game.

02:26:39.680 --> 02:26:43.480
[Guest]: Like even now my storefront, you could say,

02:26:43.680 --> 02:26:45.480
[Guest]: doesn't really have a lot of women's cricket.

02:26:45.680 --> 02:26:47.480
[Guest]: You know, I might be writing on women's cricket, yes,

02:26:47.680 --> 02:26:49.480
[Guest]: but I might be writing on other cricket also.

02:26:49.680 --> 02:26:51.480
[Guest]: I might be doing YouTube videos on cricket in general

02:26:51.480 --> 02:26:55.280
[Guest]: and where 80% of my viewers are boys, but in the background

02:26:55.480 --> 02:26:57.280
[Guest]: there are projects running where I'm thinking

02:26:57.480 --> 02:26:59.280
[Guest]: how can I make an impact on this game?

02:26:59.480 --> 02:27:03.280
[Guest]: How can I help the Indian team win a World Cup?

02:27:03.480 --> 02:27:09.280
[Guest]: How can I help the Indian domestic players get a better deal?

02:27:09.480 --> 02:27:13.280
[Guest]: Those kind of things always occupy space in my mind

02:27:13.480 --> 02:27:16.280
[Guest]: and they may not always find a creative outlet,

02:27:16.480 --> 02:27:19.280
[Guest]: but there will be something or the other running.

02:27:19.280 --> 02:27:24.080
[Guest]: And again, I'm very lucky to be able to make a living

02:27:24.280 --> 02:27:27.080
[Guest]: from this kind of thinking, just thinking about the game

02:27:27.280 --> 02:27:29.080
[Guest]: and trying to find solutions for it,

02:27:29.280 --> 02:27:33.080
[Guest]: which I really appreciate and remind myself to be grateful for.

02:27:33.280 --> 02:27:39.080
[Guest]: But that thinking process and that desire to fix the problems

02:27:39.280 --> 02:27:43.080
[Guest]: that I see in women's cricket has not really gone away

02:27:43.280 --> 02:27:46.080
[Guest]: and that's probably what is then driving

02:27:46.280 --> 02:27:48.080
[Guest]: and expressing in different ways.

02:27:48.080 --> 02:27:50.880
[Amit Varma]: So, let's talk about women's cricket.

02:27:51.080 --> 02:27:52.880
[Amit Varma]: And I almost feel hesitant, you know,

02:27:53.080 --> 02:27:54.880
[Amit Varma]: talking about women's cricket particularly

02:27:55.080 --> 02:27:56.880
[Amit Varma]: because I don't want to slot you as someone

02:27:57.080 --> 02:27:58.880
[Amit Varma]: who writes about women's cricket because like I said,

02:27:59.080 --> 02:27:59.880
[Amit Varma]: I just love your writing.

02:28:00.080 --> 02:28:01.880
[Amit Varma]: You're one of my favorite cricket writers.

02:28:02.080 --> 02:28:03.880
[Amit Varma]: But women's cricket is simply one of those subjects

02:28:04.080 --> 02:28:06.880
[Amit Varma]: which not enough people have that kind of depth of knowledge about

02:28:07.080 --> 02:28:08.880
[Amit Varma]: or sort of talk about.

02:28:09.080 --> 02:28:11.880
[Amit Varma]: You know, most Indians are kind of saturated

02:28:12.080 --> 02:28:13.880
[Amit Varma]: with the regular men's cricket that happens out there,

02:28:14.080 --> 02:28:15.880
[Amit Varma]: but know nothing about women's cricket per se.

02:28:15.880 --> 02:28:19.680
[Amit Varma]: And you've written this wonderful report called An Equal Hue

02:28:19.880 --> 02:28:22.680
[Amit Varma]: along with Karunya Keshav and the late Siddhant Patnaik.

02:28:22.880 --> 02:28:25.680
[Amit Varma]: And let's kind of talk a little bit about that

02:28:25.880 --> 02:28:27.680
[Amit Varma]: because I love reading that paper in the sense that

02:28:27.880 --> 02:28:31.680
[Amit Varma]: it laid out in great detail across all these different categories,

02:28:31.880 --> 02:28:33.680
[Amit Varma]: not just what is wrong with women's cricket,

02:28:33.880 --> 02:28:35.680
[Amit Varma]: but what can be done to improve it.

02:28:35.880 --> 02:28:38.680
[Amit Varma]: And just as a vision document and as a, you know,

02:28:38.880 --> 02:28:40.680
[Amit Varma]: taking stock of where things are,

02:28:40.880 --> 02:28:42.680
[Amit Varma]: I just found it eye-opening in many ways.

02:28:42.680 --> 02:28:46.480
[Amit Varma]: So tell me a little bit about what it involved.

02:28:46.680 --> 02:28:48.480
[Amit Varma]: Like, you know, why did you write that?

02:28:48.680 --> 02:28:50.480
[Amit Varma]: What was the impetus behind it?

02:28:50.680 --> 02:28:52.480
[Amit Varma]: Like, I know you were one of the, I think,

02:28:52.680 --> 02:28:54.480
[Amit Varma]: three journalists present during the 2017 World Cup final.

02:28:54.680 --> 02:28:56.480
[Amit Varma]: I think Karunya was also one of them.

02:28:56.680 --> 02:28:59.480
[Amit Varma]: So what was the impetus which made you decide

02:28:59.680 --> 02:29:01.480
[Amit Varma]: that this is something that needs to be done?

02:29:01.680 --> 02:29:04.480
[Amit Varma]: Did you feel that there was a serious audience for it?

02:29:04.680 --> 02:29:06.480
[Amit Varma]: Not audience in terms of eyeballs,

02:29:06.680 --> 02:29:08.480
[Amit Varma]: but in terms of people who would act in the board,

02:29:08.680 --> 02:29:10.480
[Amit Varma]: who would actually do something about it?

02:29:10.480 --> 02:29:15.280
[Amit Varma]: So tell me a little bit about what led you to the report and so on.

02:29:15.480 --> 02:29:18.280
[Guest]: So let me pick up on the fact that

02:29:18.480 --> 02:29:22.280
[Guest]: the third journalist in that 2017 World Cup was Siddhant.

02:29:22.480 --> 02:29:24.280
[Amit Varma]: Ah, so the three of you.

02:29:24.480 --> 02:29:27.280
[Guest]: Yeah. So, and that was kind of where it started

02:29:27.480 --> 02:29:30.280
[Guest]: because the two of them were working for Vision India at the time.

02:29:30.480 --> 02:29:33.280
[Guest]: I was freelancing and the three of us

02:29:33.480 --> 02:29:35.280
[Guest]: were the only ones who were traveling

02:29:35.480 --> 02:29:38.280
[Guest]: to cover the World Cup in entirety.

02:29:38.280 --> 02:29:41.080
[Guest]: Then after India reached the finals, a lot more media coverage swept in,

02:29:41.280 --> 02:29:42.080
[Guest]: which was great.

02:29:42.280 --> 02:29:45.080
[Guest]: But I must really mention here

02:29:45.280 --> 02:29:48.080
[Guest]: the influence that Siddhant also had in this entire project.

02:29:48.280 --> 02:29:51.080
[Guest]: That was the first time I actually spent time with him.

02:29:51.280 --> 02:29:53.080
[Guest]: I'd met him once in the Vision India office,

02:29:53.280 --> 02:29:56.080
[Guest]: but we were housemates on that tour.

02:29:56.280 --> 02:29:58.080
[Guest]: So we had the same schedule.

02:29:58.280 --> 02:30:00.080
[Guest]: So we basically had planned our accommodation

02:30:00.280 --> 02:30:02.080
[Guest]: and our travel, etc. together.

02:30:02.280 --> 02:30:04.080
[Guest]: And we chatted so much about women's cricket.

02:30:04.280 --> 02:30:06.080
[Guest]: And of course, he was, I mean, not there just because

02:30:06.080 --> 02:30:07.880
[Guest]: he was working with Vision India.

02:30:08.080 --> 02:30:09.880
[Guest]: Even before that, in all his time,

02:30:10.080 --> 02:30:13.880
[Guest]: he and Karun had put up a huge body of work

02:30:14.080 --> 02:30:14.880
[Guest]: on women's cricket.

02:30:15.080 --> 02:30:16.880
[Guest]: They were one of the few people who were writing about

02:30:17.080 --> 02:30:19.880
[Guest]: domestic women's cricket, international women's cricket

02:30:20.080 --> 02:30:20.880
[Guest]: before 2017.

02:30:21.080 --> 02:30:22.880
[Guest]: Remember, 2017 is the moment where

02:30:23.080 --> 02:30:24.880
[Guest]: women's cricket became cool again.

02:30:25.080 --> 02:30:26.880
[Guest]: And I'm always going to have tremendous respect

02:30:27.080 --> 02:30:28.880
[Guest]: for the people who were putting in a lot of work

02:30:29.080 --> 02:30:29.880
[Guest]: behind the scenes before that.

02:30:30.080 --> 02:30:30.880
[Guest]: And Siddhant was one of those people.

02:30:31.080 --> 02:30:33.880
[Guest]: And he has a sister who, you know,

02:30:33.880 --> 02:30:36.680
[Guest]: he saw a lot of similarities between her and me.

02:30:36.880 --> 02:30:39.680
[Guest]: This sporty kid, always not afraid to play

02:30:39.880 --> 02:30:41.680
[Guest]: with the boys, standing out.

02:30:41.880 --> 02:30:43.680
[Guest]: And there was always this desire to kind of make

02:30:43.880 --> 02:30:46.680
[Guest]: the world a better place for people like her.

02:30:46.880 --> 02:30:50.680
[Guest]: And therefore, this kinship with the underdogs,

02:30:50.880 --> 02:30:53.680
[Guest]: whether it's domestic men's cricketers

02:30:53.880 --> 02:30:55.680
[Guest]: or women's international cricketers.

02:30:55.880 --> 02:30:59.680
[Guest]: And so the loss of the 2017 World Cup final,

02:30:59.880 --> 02:31:01.680
[Guest]: even for that final, the three of us were

02:31:01.680 --> 02:31:04.480
[Guest]: sharing a house together in London.

02:31:04.680 --> 02:31:07.480
[Guest]: And we kind of grieved it in that final

02:31:07.680 --> 02:31:08.480
[Guest]: in our own ways.

02:31:08.680 --> 02:31:11.480
[Guest]: I remember finishing my filing

02:31:11.680 --> 02:31:14.480
[Guest]: at some ridiculous hour at night

02:31:14.680 --> 02:31:17.480
[Guest]: and after that match, just collapsing

02:31:17.680 --> 02:31:18.480
[Guest]: in the kitchen and crying.

02:31:18.680 --> 02:31:20.480
[Guest]: I mean, that is the time where the emotion

02:31:20.680 --> 02:31:21.480
[Guest]: finally came out that, you know,

02:31:21.680 --> 02:31:25.480
[Guest]: we were so close and we lost by nine runs.

02:31:25.680 --> 02:31:27.480
[Guest]: And after that, we kept talking,

02:31:27.680 --> 02:31:29.480
[Guest]: especially Siddhant and me, about

02:31:29.480 --> 02:31:32.280
[Guest]: what we can do to help the game,

02:31:32.480 --> 02:31:35.280
[Guest]: what we can do to try and make it better.

02:31:35.480 --> 02:31:37.280
[Guest]: So, I mean, for a start, we decided,

02:31:37.480 --> 02:31:39.280
[Guest]: OK, let's compile our suggestions

02:31:39.480 --> 02:31:40.280
[Guest]: for whatever it's worth.

02:31:40.480 --> 02:31:43.280
[Guest]: And we made a very rough document

02:31:43.480 --> 02:31:44.280
[Guest]: which had some excellent suggestions.

02:31:44.480 --> 02:31:47.280
[Guest]: I mean, even Siddhant had really put in,

02:31:47.480 --> 02:31:49.280
[Guest]: you know, he had event management background.

02:31:49.480 --> 02:31:51.280
[Guest]: So use that kind of a background

02:31:51.480 --> 02:31:53.280
[Guest]: to draw this up.

02:31:53.480 --> 02:31:55.280
[Guest]: He happened to speak to Nandan Kamath,

02:31:55.480 --> 02:31:57.280
[Guest]: who you've had on your pod before,

02:31:57.280 --> 02:32:00.080
[Guest]: who has founded something called

02:32:00.280 --> 02:32:02.080
[Guest]: the Sports Law and Policy Center,

02:32:02.280 --> 02:32:04.080
[Guest]: which is a body which is dedicated

02:32:04.280 --> 02:32:06.080
[Guest]: to kind of publishing these kind of works

02:32:06.280 --> 02:32:09.080
[Guest]: which create almost a body of work

02:32:09.280 --> 02:32:11.080
[Guest]: on that particular sport.

02:32:11.280 --> 02:32:13.080
[Guest]: So Nandan really encouraged us

02:32:13.280 --> 02:32:15.080
[Guest]: to widen and deepen the scope of the report

02:32:15.280 --> 02:32:17.080
[Guest]: and make it, you know,

02:32:17.280 --> 02:32:19.080
[Guest]: a basic groundwork document

02:32:19.280 --> 02:32:21.080
[Guest]: where anyone who wants to have

02:32:21.280 --> 02:32:23.080
[Guest]: any kind of influence in women's cricket

02:32:23.280 --> 02:32:26.080
[Guest]: can read this, get an idea of where they are,

02:32:26.080 --> 02:32:28.880
[Guest]: where the action areas are required.

02:32:29.080 --> 02:32:31.880
[Guest]: And so we set about that.

02:32:32.080 --> 02:32:34.880
[Guest]: During the course of making that report,

02:32:35.080 --> 02:32:36.880
[Guest]: Siddhant's sickness got worse

02:32:37.080 --> 02:32:39.880
[Guest]: and eventually he didn't survive.

02:32:40.080 --> 02:32:42.880
[Guest]: After that, I asked Arunia to come on board

02:32:43.080 --> 02:32:44.880
[Guest]: and the two of us kind of finished that work.

02:32:45.080 --> 02:32:46.880
[Guest]: And during the course of the lockdown,

02:32:47.080 --> 02:32:48.880
[Guest]: actually, when we both got a lot more time,

02:32:49.080 --> 02:32:50.880
[Guest]: so a project that was kind of

02:32:51.080 --> 02:32:52.880
[Guest]: in the making for three years,

02:32:53.080 --> 02:32:53.880
[Guest]: put it together,

02:32:53.880 --> 02:32:56.680
[Guest]: we based it not just on our own experience,

02:32:56.880 --> 02:32:59.680
[Guest]: but a survey conducted of 350 state cricketers

02:32:59.880 --> 02:33:02.680
[Guest]: who were really generous with our time.

02:33:02.880 --> 02:33:04.680
[Guest]: Again, like the sense of community

02:33:04.880 --> 02:33:06.680
[Guest]: within the women's cricket circuit

02:33:06.880 --> 02:33:10.680
[Guest]: where they all volunteered to fill up the survey

02:33:10.880 --> 02:33:12.680
[Guest]: because, again, there was a lot of goodwill

02:33:12.880 --> 02:33:14.680
[Guest]: built up by Arunia and Siddhant also

02:33:14.880 --> 02:33:16.680
[Guest]: in the process of writing their book.

02:33:16.880 --> 02:33:18.680
[Guest]: So when they knew that they were involved in this,

02:33:18.880 --> 02:33:21.680
[Guest]: a lot of cricketers participated very actively.

02:33:21.680 --> 02:33:24.480
[Guest]: And this kind of then led us to

02:33:24.680 --> 02:33:25.480
[Guest]: the Equal Hue Report,

02:33:25.680 --> 02:33:27.480
[Guest]: which was published in 2020.

02:33:27.680 --> 02:33:31.480
[Guest]: It is the groundwork for action

02:33:31.680 --> 02:33:32.480
[Guest]: that needs to be taken next.

02:33:32.680 --> 02:33:34.480
[Guest]: It's a document that analyzes

02:33:34.680 --> 02:33:35.480
[Guest]: where the gap areas are.

02:33:35.680 --> 02:33:37.480
[Guest]: It's the document that really says

02:33:37.680 --> 02:33:39.480
[Guest]: that, you know, OK, if anyone,

02:33:39.680 --> 02:33:40.480
[Guest]: whether it's the BCCI,

02:33:40.680 --> 02:33:41.480
[Guest]: whether it's a broadcaster,

02:33:41.680 --> 02:33:44.480
[Guest]: whether it's some NGO who wants to do good work,

02:33:44.680 --> 02:33:46.480
[Guest]: or whether it's a corporate who has CSR funds,

02:33:46.680 --> 02:33:49.480
[Guest]: they would like to use it to help women's cricket grow.

02:33:49.480 --> 02:33:51.280
[Guest]: These are the areas where you can start.

02:33:51.480 --> 02:33:53.280
[Guest]: This is the way where you can make an impact

02:33:53.480 --> 02:33:55.280
[Guest]: through the recommendations that we've made.

02:33:55.480 --> 02:33:56.280
[Guest]: Along the way, you know,

02:33:56.480 --> 02:33:57.280
[Guest]: we've also had this sense of,

02:33:57.480 --> 02:33:59.280
[Guest]: OK, now we've done this analysis,

02:33:59.480 --> 02:34:00.280
[Guest]: now what?

02:34:00.480 --> 02:34:02.280
[Guest]: And therefore, it's moved into action.

02:34:02.480 --> 02:34:05.280
[Guest]: And we've formed, Karunia, myself,

02:34:05.480 --> 02:34:07.280
[Guest]: people at the Sports Law Policy Center

02:34:07.480 --> 02:34:08.280
[Guest]: have formed the Equal Hue Project

02:34:08.480 --> 02:34:11.280
[Guest]: where we are trying to fill some of these gaps ourselves.

02:34:11.480 --> 02:34:15.280
[Guest]: And a couple of the gaps that we identified were

02:34:15.480 --> 02:34:18.280
[Guest]: not enough information about women's cricket, you know.

02:34:18.280 --> 02:34:20.080
[Guest]: If a women's cricketer is sitting in

02:34:20.280 --> 02:34:24.080
[Guest]: Cuttack, Bhubaneswar, Orissa or Dharamshala,

02:34:24.280 --> 02:34:26.080
[Guest]: do they know the pathways in their state?

02:34:26.280 --> 02:34:28.080
[Guest]: So, Karunia really headed a project

02:34:28.280 --> 02:34:31.080
[Guest]: which compiled information for each state

02:34:31.280 --> 02:34:34.080
[Guest]: of, you know, what the existing pathways in that state are,

02:34:34.280 --> 02:34:37.080
[Guest]: how a woman who's interested in cricket

02:34:37.280 --> 02:34:38.080
[Guest]: or a girl who's interested in cricket

02:34:38.280 --> 02:34:40.080
[Guest]: can find cricket near her,

02:34:40.280 --> 02:34:43.080
[Guest]: what the state association processes are,

02:34:43.280 --> 02:34:44.080
[Guest]: what their phone numbers are,

02:34:44.280 --> 02:34:45.080
[Guest]: wherever available,

02:34:45.280 --> 02:34:46.080
[Guest]: whatever information is available

02:34:46.080 --> 02:34:48.880
[Guest]: has been put together in a website,

02:34:49.080 --> 02:34:49.880
[Guest]: on the Equal Hue website,

02:34:50.080 --> 02:34:52.880
[Guest]: where, you know, we're aiming to fill up that information gap.

02:34:53.080 --> 02:34:56.880
[Guest]: They also worked really hard on publishing an audiobook

02:34:57.080 --> 02:34:58.880
[Guest]: where there's a women's cricketer

02:34:59.080 --> 02:35:00.880
[Guest]: as a central figure in it

02:35:01.080 --> 02:35:02.880
[Guest]: for 5 to 8-year-olds or 5 to 10-year-olds.

02:35:03.080 --> 02:35:05.880
[Guest]: So, the next generation should grow up

02:35:06.080 --> 02:35:07.880
[Guest]: with women's cricketers in their consciousness.

02:35:08.080 --> 02:35:08.880
[Guest]: So, that's some of the projects

02:35:09.080 --> 02:35:10.880
[Guest]: that the Equal Hue Project is working on.

02:35:11.080 --> 02:35:12.880
[Guest]: Like I said, there are projects in the background

02:35:13.080 --> 02:35:13.880
[Guest]: that we are working on.

02:35:13.880 --> 02:35:17.680
[Guest]: We have plans and we are reaching out

02:35:17.880 --> 02:35:19.680
[Guest]: to various brands to partner with them

02:35:19.880 --> 02:35:22.680
[Guest]: on these plans to just support the ecosystem

02:35:22.880 --> 02:35:23.680
[Guest]: more and more,

02:35:23.880 --> 02:35:24.680
[Guest]: be it through scholarships,

02:35:24.880 --> 02:35:25.680
[Guest]: be it through tournaments.

02:35:25.880 --> 02:35:28.680
[Guest]: And that's, I think, the big opportunity

02:35:28.880 --> 02:35:31.680
[Guest]: and something that I hope really allows us

02:35:31.880 --> 02:35:33.680
[Guest]: to make an actual impact on the ground

02:35:33.880 --> 02:35:35.680
[Guest]: because there's only so much you can do

02:35:35.880 --> 02:35:38.680
[Guest]: is what I've discovered writing about a sport.

02:35:38.880 --> 02:35:41.680
[Guest]: But, you know, can we actually make an impact

02:35:41.680 --> 02:35:44.480
[Guest]: on the ground through our projects?

02:35:44.680 --> 02:35:47.480
[Guest]: That's the new focus almost.

02:35:47.680 --> 02:35:49.480
[Amit Varma]: You know, the hope has been voiced by many

02:35:49.680 --> 02:35:51.480
[Amit Varma]: that the 2017 World Cup final

02:35:51.680 --> 02:35:53.480
[Amit Varma]: with all the viewership that it got and so on,

02:35:53.680 --> 02:35:55.480
[Amit Varma]: the World Cup, in fact, not just the final,

02:35:55.680 --> 02:35:56.480
[Amit Varma]: with all the viewership that it got

02:35:56.680 --> 02:35:58.480
[Amit Varma]: could be something like the 1983 moment

02:35:58.680 --> 02:36:00.480
[Amit Varma]: for men's cricket was.

02:36:00.680 --> 02:36:01.480
[Amit Varma]: But my question is, you know,

02:36:01.680 --> 02:36:05.480
[Amit Varma]: I think in the life of any sport or any activity,

02:36:05.680 --> 02:36:08.480
[Amit Varma]: there is this transition from where early on

02:36:08.680 --> 02:36:10.480
[Amit Varma]: all the people who care about it deeply

02:36:10.480 --> 02:36:12.280
[Amit Varma]: and are making initiatives are people

02:36:12.480 --> 02:36:13.280
[Amit Varma]: who are just passionate about it

02:36:13.480 --> 02:36:15.280
[Amit Varma]: and are motivated by that passion

02:36:15.480 --> 02:36:16.280
[Amit Varma]: and that's what's driving them.

02:36:16.480 --> 02:36:18.280
[Amit Varma]: And then the next phase that comes

02:36:18.480 --> 02:36:21.280
[Amit Varma]: is when it crosses a certain tipping point

02:36:21.480 --> 02:36:23.280
[Amit Varma]: and people are instead motivated by commerce.

02:36:23.480 --> 02:36:25.280
[Amit Varma]: You know, so people begin to do things

02:36:25.480 --> 02:36:26.280
[Amit Varma]: for women's cricket

02:36:26.480 --> 02:36:28.280
[Amit Varma]: because they feel there is a market for it

02:36:28.480 --> 02:36:30.280
[Amit Varma]: and then things really improve,

02:36:30.480 --> 02:36:32.280
[Amit Varma]: then infrastructure improves,

02:36:32.480 --> 02:36:33.280
[Amit Varma]: then all of these things, you know,

02:36:33.480 --> 02:36:35.280
[Amit Varma]: like you've got a section

02:36:35.480 --> 02:36:37.280
[Amit Varma]: where you speak about barriers to participation

02:36:37.480 --> 02:36:38.280
[Amit Varma]: which include cultural barriers,

02:36:38.280 --> 02:36:41.080
[Amit Varma]: physical barriers, financial barriers,

02:36:41.280 --> 02:36:43.080
[Amit Varma]: then those start to disappear.

02:36:43.280 --> 02:36:44.080
[Amit Varma]: You've got a section where you talk about

02:36:44.280 --> 02:36:46.080
[Amit Varma]: domestic cricket and the grassroots

02:36:46.280 --> 02:36:49.080
[Amit Varma]: and how the ecosystem there can be much better

02:36:49.280 --> 02:36:52.080
[Amit Varma]: and those kind of start to vanish.

02:36:52.280 --> 02:36:53.080
[Amit Varma]: So how close is that point?

02:36:53.280 --> 02:36:54.080
[Amit Varma]: Have we reached that point?

02:36:54.280 --> 02:36:55.080
[Amit Varma]: Have we crossed that point?

02:36:55.280 --> 02:36:57.080
[Amit Varma]: Is it still somewhere in the future?

02:36:57.280 --> 02:36:59.080
[Amit Varma]: Give me a sense of how the game

02:36:59.280 --> 02:37:02.080
[Amit Varma]: is sort of evolving in that sense

02:37:02.280 --> 02:37:04.080
[Amit Varma]: because it is true that women's cricket

02:37:04.280 --> 02:37:06.080
[Amit Varma]: is much more in the consciousness

02:37:06.080 --> 02:37:07.880
[Amit Varma]: of a lot of viewers,

02:37:08.080 --> 02:37:10.880
[Amit Varma]: but is there enough women's cricket happening?

02:37:11.080 --> 02:37:12.880
[Amit Varma]: Are they watching it actively?

02:37:13.080 --> 02:37:15.880
[Amit Varma]: What's the ecosystem like beneath the elite game?

02:37:16.080 --> 02:37:18.880
[Amit Varma]: Give me a little bit of a sense of that.

02:37:19.080 --> 02:37:21.880
[Guest]: So let me answer the

02:37:22.080 --> 02:37:24.880
[Guest]: driven by commerce kind of angle first.

02:37:25.080 --> 02:37:28.880
[Guest]: The last IPL T20 women's challenge that happened

02:37:29.080 --> 02:37:31.880
[Guest]: where it involved three teams

02:37:31.880 --> 02:37:36.680
[Guest]: was held in Dubai alongside the men's IPL of 2020.

02:37:36.880 --> 02:37:39.680
[Guest]: It was the first tournament to attract sponsors.

02:37:39.880 --> 02:37:41.680
[Guest]: It was the first tournament where Jio came on board

02:37:41.880 --> 02:37:43.680
[Guest]: as an independent title sponsor.

02:37:43.880 --> 02:37:45.680
[Guest]: It was very prudent and smart of the BCCI

02:37:45.880 --> 02:37:48.680
[Guest]: to not just piggyback it along with the men's tournament

02:37:48.880 --> 02:37:50.680
[Guest]: and the men's sponsors and identify it

02:37:50.880 --> 02:37:52.680
[Guest]: as a separate property and see what value

02:37:52.880 --> 02:37:55.680
[Guest]: there is for this property.

02:37:55.880 --> 02:37:57.680
[Guest]: Jio came on board as a title sponsor

02:37:57.880 --> 02:37:59.680
[Guest]: and then all the IPL supporting sponsors

02:37:59.680 --> 02:38:02.480
[Guest]: came on board for this women's T20 challenge as well.

02:38:02.680 --> 02:38:05.480
[Guest]: Wonderful opportunity for you to get branding.

02:38:05.680 --> 02:38:07.480
[Guest]: Wonderful opportunity for you to get exposure

02:38:07.680 --> 02:38:10.480
[Guest]: and what the BCCI treasurer I believe said after the tournament

02:38:10.680 --> 02:38:12.480
[Guest]: is this is now financially sustainable

02:38:12.680 --> 02:38:15.480
[Guest]: which I take to understand that it paid for itself.

02:38:15.680 --> 02:38:17.480
[Guest]: We've broken even.

02:38:17.680 --> 02:38:22.480
[Guest]: So if that is the bare minimum of where we are,

02:38:22.680 --> 02:38:24.480
[Guest]: it's a wonderful starting point to be

02:38:24.680 --> 02:38:28.480
[Guest]: because you can just everything north of this is profit.

02:38:28.480 --> 02:38:31.280
[Guest]: So I think commerce wise that is where

02:38:31.480 --> 02:38:36.280
[Guest]: the Indian team is value wise when right now

02:38:36.480 --> 02:38:38.280
[Guest]: it's hard to define a separate value

02:38:38.480 --> 02:38:40.280
[Guest]: for the Indian women's cricket team because

02:38:40.480 --> 02:38:42.280
[Guest]: how do you define value of a sports property?

02:38:42.480 --> 02:38:44.280
[Guest]: Broadcast rights.

02:38:44.480 --> 02:38:47.280
[Guest]: What kind of money is being paid by broadcasters

02:38:47.480 --> 02:38:49.280
[Guest]: to showcase this property which reflects

02:38:49.480 --> 02:38:52.280
[Guest]: how many advertisers are willing to put money

02:38:52.480 --> 02:38:54.280
[Guest]: behind this kind of a product.

02:38:54.480 --> 02:38:56.280
[Guest]: It's hard to gauge right now because

02:38:56.280 --> 02:38:59.080
[Guest]: women's domestic women's international matches

02:38:59.280 --> 02:39:02.080
[Guest]: are bundled in to the men's broadcast rights

02:39:02.280 --> 02:39:05.080
[Guest]: along with you know, the under 19 World Cup

02:39:05.280 --> 02:39:08.080
[Guest]: or those under 19 teams same with the shirt sponsorship.

02:39:08.280 --> 02:39:11.080
[Guest]: The shirt sponsorship is sold as a bundle

02:39:11.280 --> 02:39:14.080
[Guest]: for the men's women's and under 19.

02:39:14.280 --> 02:39:16.080
[Guest]: Whereas I think now in the next cycle

02:39:16.280 --> 02:39:18.080
[Guest]: which is 2023 onwards.

02:39:18.280 --> 02:39:20.080
[Guest]: There is a case.

02:39:20.280 --> 02:39:23.080
[Guest]: There is a strong case to separate this

02:39:23.280 --> 02:39:24.080
[Guest]: as a separate property.

02:39:24.080 --> 02:39:26.880
[Guest]: Let's say women's cricket is sold at a separate property.

02:39:27.080 --> 02:39:27.880
[Guest]: It will earn you.

02:39:28.080 --> 02:39:29.880
[Guest]: I mean by separating women's cricket

02:39:30.080 --> 02:39:31.880
[Guest]: the overall cost of the men's rights

02:39:32.080 --> 02:39:32.880
[Guest]: is not going to come down.

02:39:33.080 --> 02:39:34.880
[Guest]: Yeah, but the but the women's rights

02:39:35.080 --> 02:39:37.880
[Guest]: might earn you, you know, some amount of money.

02:39:38.080 --> 02:39:39.880
[Guest]: It's not going to be in the range of what the men

02:39:40.080 --> 02:39:41.880
[Guest]: men's rights are going to earn you,

02:39:42.080 --> 02:39:43.880
[Guest]: but it will earn you some amount of money

02:39:44.080 --> 02:39:46.880
[Guest]: that will put a number on the value of women's cricket

02:39:47.080 --> 02:39:48.880
[Guest]: and that is something I look forward to happening.

02:39:49.080 --> 02:39:51.880
[Guest]: There's also the fact that if you look at

02:39:52.080 --> 02:39:52.880
[Guest]: a women's cricket broadcast now,

02:39:52.880 --> 02:39:54.680
[Guest]: for example, on these OTT apps,

02:39:54.880 --> 02:39:58.680
[Guest]: you can you can gauge that by how many of these

02:39:58.880 --> 02:40:02.680
[Guest]: how many ads are off the OTT platform itself.

02:40:02.880 --> 02:40:05.680
[Guest]: For example, if it's a on Hotstar in the breaks,

02:40:05.880 --> 02:40:07.680
[Guest]: how many Hotstar ads are you seeing?

02:40:07.880 --> 02:40:10.680
[Guest]: Because that is time where they haven't been able

02:40:10.880 --> 02:40:11.680
[Guest]: to sell it to an advertiser.

02:40:11.880 --> 02:40:13.680
[Guest]: So they put a Hotstar ad there.

02:40:13.880 --> 02:40:15.680
[Guest]: So if you see a lot of Hotstar ads,

02:40:15.880 --> 02:40:17.680
[Guest]: it means that this property is not really valuable.

02:40:17.880 --> 02:40:21.680
[Guest]: What I've seen is of the recent tour to Australia.

02:40:21.680 --> 02:40:24.480
[Guest]: There were a lot of ads for the women's tour to Australia.

02:40:24.680 --> 02:40:26.480
[Guest]: There were ads by brands,

02:40:26.680 --> 02:40:28.480
[Guest]: very few ads by the broadcaster who was Sony.

02:40:28.680 --> 02:40:32.480
[Guest]: There was also title sponsors for the series.

02:40:32.680 --> 02:40:35.480
[Guest]: There was also investment by the broadcaster

02:40:35.680 --> 02:40:37.480
[Guest]: in building up this is for away series.

02:40:37.680 --> 02:40:41.480
[Guest]: Hindi, Tamil, Telugu, three separate languages

02:40:41.680 --> 02:40:44.480
[Guest]: for broadcast for the women's series

02:40:44.680 --> 02:40:47.480
[Guest]: beyond just the world feed English commentary

02:40:47.680 --> 02:40:50.480
[Guest]: that they carry, which tells me that's where you

02:40:50.480 --> 02:40:52.280
[Guest]: that's where they stand in terms of commerce

02:40:52.480 --> 02:40:55.280
[Guest]: in terms of the underlying structure.

02:40:55.480 --> 02:40:57.280
[Guest]: So much that could be better.

02:40:57.480 --> 02:41:00.280
[Guest]: I mean, we talk about the strength of domestic cricket

02:41:00.480 --> 02:41:03.280
[Guest]: for the men and the finishing school

02:41:03.480 --> 02:41:06.280
[Guest]: that is the IPL and the India A programs

02:41:06.480 --> 02:41:09.280
[Guest]: a long time ago for the men's in men's cricket.

02:41:09.480 --> 02:41:12.280
[Guest]: We used to compare Australia as a better domestic system.

02:41:12.480 --> 02:41:15.280
[Guest]: Why? Because they have only eight teams,

02:41:15.480 --> 02:41:17.280
[Guest]: whereas we have some 30-35 teams

02:41:17.480 --> 02:41:19.280
[Guest]: and we are diluting our talent.

02:41:19.280 --> 02:41:23.080
[Guest]: Therefore, the competition is less fierce.

02:41:23.280 --> 02:41:25.080
[Guest]: Therefore, the players are not battle hardened

02:41:25.280 --> 02:41:27.080
[Guest]: when they come to international cricket.

02:41:27.280 --> 02:41:28.080
[Guest]: What has changed?

02:41:28.280 --> 02:41:30.080
[Guest]: I mean, we still have 30-35 teams,

02:41:30.280 --> 02:41:32.080
[Guest]: but now we have an India A program.

02:41:32.280 --> 02:41:33.080
[Guest]: Now we have an IPL.

02:41:33.280 --> 02:41:35.080
[Guest]: Those are the steps up.

02:41:35.280 --> 02:41:37.080
[Guest]: So, I mean, for me, it's just common sense to say

02:41:37.280 --> 02:41:39.080
[Guest]: that, you know, apply the same model here.

02:41:39.280 --> 02:41:42.080
[Guest]: We have 30-35 teams playing domestic cricket.

02:41:42.280 --> 02:41:44.080
[Guest]: Please have an India A program.

02:41:44.280 --> 02:41:45.080
[Guest]: Please have an under-19 program.

02:41:45.280 --> 02:41:47.080
[Guest]: Please have a women's IPL and just see how,

02:41:47.080 --> 02:41:50.880
[Guest]: you know, other countries are scared of India getting it right

02:41:51.080 --> 02:41:53.880
[Guest]: because of just the sheer number of players that we have,

02:41:54.080 --> 02:41:55.880
[Guest]: even despite, you know, not really trying.

02:41:56.080 --> 02:41:58.880
[Guest]: A few moves which have bewildered me

02:41:59.080 --> 02:42:00.880
[Guest]: in the last few years have been

02:42:01.080 --> 02:42:03.880
[Guest]: the removal of the interzonal tournament.

02:42:04.080 --> 02:42:05.880
[Guest]: So, from these 30-35 teams,

02:42:06.080 --> 02:42:06.880
[Guest]: you're picking talent directly,

02:42:07.080 --> 02:42:08.880
[Guest]: putting it in the challenger trophy

02:42:09.080 --> 02:42:10.880
[Guest]: and sending it to international level.

02:42:11.080 --> 02:42:13.880
[Guest]: Of course, they're going to find that jump slightly difficult.

02:42:14.080 --> 02:42:15.880
[Guest]: The interzonal level was what gave them

02:42:15.880 --> 02:42:17.680
[Guest]: a little bit of a stepping stone.

02:42:17.880 --> 02:42:20.680
[Guest]: I would love to see that tournament come back

02:42:20.880 --> 02:42:22.680
[Guest]: besides the fact that it just gives more match days

02:42:22.880 --> 02:42:23.680
[Guest]: to the players.

02:42:23.880 --> 02:42:25.680
[Guest]: Again, they play too few matches.

02:42:25.880 --> 02:42:27.680
[Guest]: Spend nine months of the year training

02:42:27.880 --> 02:42:29.680
[Guest]: and play about four or five matches ODI,

02:42:29.880 --> 02:42:31.680
[Guest]: four or five matches T20.

02:42:31.880 --> 02:42:32.680
[Guest]: If you don't qualify for the next stage,

02:42:32.880 --> 02:42:34.680
[Guest]: that's it. Domestic season over

02:42:34.880 --> 02:42:36.680
[Guest]: in senior cricket.

02:42:36.880 --> 02:42:40.680
[Guest]: And what was your other question about the underlying structure or...

02:42:40.880 --> 02:42:43.680
[Amit Varma]: I'll come back to that just to follow on sort of,

02:42:43.680 --> 02:42:46.480
[Amit Varma]: you know, what you said obviously makes sense

02:42:46.680 --> 02:42:47.480
[Amit Varma]: that if you unbundle the rights,

02:42:47.680 --> 02:42:50.480
[Amit Varma]: you get a proper picture of where

02:42:50.680 --> 02:42:51.480
[Amit Varma]: women's cricket really stands.

02:42:51.680 --> 02:42:54.480
[Amit Varma]: And therefore, the risk of underestimating it

02:42:54.680 --> 02:42:55.480
[Amit Varma]: is no longer there.

02:42:55.680 --> 02:42:57.480
[Amit Varma]: You know, is it then a problem that BCCI

02:42:57.680 --> 02:42:59.480
[Amit Varma]: is running both aspects of the game?

02:42:59.680 --> 02:43:00.480
[Amit Varma]: Because obviously, I'm, you know,

02:43:00.680 --> 02:43:02.480
[Amit Varma]: both men's cricket and women's cricket

02:43:02.680 --> 02:43:04.480
[Amit Varma]: because I get it that in 2006,

02:43:04.680 --> 02:43:05.480
[Amit Varma]: with all the resources,

02:43:05.680 --> 02:43:07.480
[Amit Varma]: they improved a lot of things.

02:43:07.680 --> 02:43:09.480
[Amit Varma]: They can't take a lot of the abundant money

02:43:09.680 --> 02:43:11.480
[Amit Varma]: from the men's game and, you know,

02:43:11.480 --> 02:43:13.480
[Amit Varma]: use it to give the women's game a leg up.

02:43:13.680 --> 02:43:16.280
[Amit Varma]: But if I just think of incentives within the BCCI,

02:43:16.480 --> 02:43:18.280
[Amit Varma]: their huge cash cow is the men's game.

02:43:18.480 --> 02:43:21.280
[Amit Varma]: All their thinking, all their organizational work,

02:43:21.480 --> 02:43:24.280
[Amit Varma]: it's natural for it to kind of go there.

02:43:24.480 --> 02:43:26.280
[Amit Varma]: So was it perhaps better earlier

02:43:26.480 --> 02:43:28.280
[Amit Varma]: in just in terms of incentives

02:43:28.480 --> 02:43:30.280
[Amit Varma]: that if you have a body where, you know,

02:43:30.480 --> 02:43:32.280
[Amit Varma]: your job is women's cricket, it's nothing else.

02:43:32.480 --> 02:43:33.280
[Amit Varma]: That's all you do.

02:43:33.480 --> 02:43:34.280
[Amit Varma]: That's your incentives.

02:43:34.480 --> 02:43:35.280
[Amit Varma]: That's how you will be judged.

02:43:35.480 --> 02:43:36.280
[Amit Varma]: It's a separate product.

02:43:36.480 --> 02:43:38.280
[Amit Varma]: It's a separate property, you know.

02:43:38.280 --> 02:43:41.280
[Amit Varma]: So do you see that as a structural flaw?

02:43:41.480 --> 02:43:45.080
[Amit Varma]: Does the BCCI really take women's cricket that seriously?

02:43:45.280 --> 02:43:47.080
[Amit Varma]: What's your sense?

02:43:47.280 --> 02:43:49.080
[Guest]: This is an interesting line of thinking

02:43:49.280 --> 02:43:52.080
[Guest]: and it's something that the cricket historian

02:43:52.280 --> 02:43:55.080
[Guest]: in the UK, Raf Nicholson, has researched quite a bit.

02:43:55.280 --> 02:44:00.080
[Guest]: She's actually, I think, doing something close to a thesis

02:44:00.280 --> 02:44:04.080
[Guest]: on how women's sport has fared

02:44:04.280 --> 02:44:07.080
[Guest]: after it kind of got absorbed by the ruling

02:44:07.080 --> 02:44:08.880
[Guest]: existing men's body.

02:44:09.080 --> 02:44:10.880
[Guest]: And like I've said, there are a lot of things

02:44:11.080 --> 02:44:12.880
[Guest]: that, you know, change for the better

02:44:13.080 --> 02:44:15.880
[Guest]: and there are some things that change for the worse.

02:44:16.080 --> 02:44:18.880
[Guest]: In terms of incentives, if you really go that cold,

02:44:19.080 --> 02:44:21.880
[Guest]: I'm trying to put my passion for women's cricket aside.

02:44:22.080 --> 02:44:25.880
[Guest]: Think about it in terms of a commercial property.

02:44:26.080 --> 02:44:27.880
[Guest]: Think about it in terms of, you know,

02:44:28.080 --> 02:44:29.880
[Guest]: can this earn me revenue?

02:44:30.080 --> 02:44:33.880
[Guest]: Is it worth putting in X amount of money

02:44:33.880 --> 02:44:37.680
[Guest]: and will I get greater than X back?

02:44:37.880 --> 02:44:39.680
[Guest]: Initially, no.

02:44:39.880 --> 02:44:41.680
[Guest]: Initially, it's going to be something that requires

02:44:41.880 --> 02:44:43.680
[Guest]: a lot of investment of time and money to grow.

02:44:43.880 --> 02:44:46.680
[Guest]: But the potential of women's cricket as a property,

02:44:46.880 --> 02:44:49.680
[Guest]: I think, is something that people are missing

02:44:49.880 --> 02:44:53.680
[Guest]: and you have to kind of think about it

02:44:53.880 --> 02:44:56.680
[Guest]: in terms of doubling your base

02:44:56.880 --> 02:45:01.680
[Guest]: rather than, you know, draining your resources.

02:45:01.680 --> 02:45:04.480
[Guest]: So if one thinks about it like that,

02:45:04.680 --> 02:45:07.480
[Guest]: we've seen how women's sport has just grown

02:45:07.680 --> 02:45:09.480
[Guest]: into its own cash-generating,

02:45:09.680 --> 02:45:12.480
[Guest]: revenue-generating property in other sports.

02:45:12.680 --> 02:45:15.480
[Guest]: We've seen the success of the women's Big Bash League.

02:45:15.680 --> 02:45:18.480
[Guest]: We've seen the popularity of the US

02:45:18.680 --> 02:45:20.480
[Guest]: national women's football team.

02:45:20.680 --> 02:45:23.480
[Guest]: We've seen PV Sindhu as, you know,

02:45:23.680 --> 02:45:25.480
[Guest]: a female sport icon, although team sport,

02:45:25.680 --> 02:45:27.480
[Guest]: I'll probably, should probably take more examples

02:45:27.680 --> 02:45:29.480
[Guest]: from team sport.

02:45:29.480 --> 02:45:32.280
[Guest]: But there is enough to suggest,

02:45:32.480 --> 02:45:34.280
[Guest]: like we saw with the IPL,

02:45:34.480 --> 02:45:36.280
[Guest]: where sponsors came on for just,

02:45:36.480 --> 02:45:38.280
[Guest]: which essentially exhibition matches.

02:45:38.480 --> 02:45:41.280
[Guest]: There is enough to suggest that there is value

02:45:41.480 --> 02:45:43.280
[Guest]: in putting in this investment for 4 or 5 years.

02:45:43.480 --> 02:45:46.280
[Guest]: There are incentives to put in that investment

02:45:46.480 --> 02:45:47.280
[Guest]: for 4 or 5 years.

02:45:47.480 --> 02:45:49.280
[Guest]: Think about it from an IPL team.

02:45:49.480 --> 02:45:51.280
[Guest]: Okay, suppose an IPL team wants to,

02:45:51.480 --> 02:45:53.280
[Guest]: or, you know, what are the incentives

02:45:53.480 --> 02:45:55.280
[Guest]: for an IPL team to start a women's cricket team?

02:45:55.280 --> 02:46:00.080
[Guest]: One is that IPL is only a 2-month-a-year property.

02:46:00.280 --> 02:46:02.080
[Guest]: If you can double that for a small investment,

02:46:02.280 --> 02:46:04.080
[Guest]: getting involved with a women's IPL

02:46:04.280 --> 02:46:05.080
[Guest]: will require a smaller investment

02:46:05.280 --> 02:46:06.080
[Guest]: than it was for a men's investment.

02:46:06.280 --> 02:46:09.080
[Guest]: You're doubling your branding suddenly

02:46:09.280 --> 02:46:11.080
[Guest]: because if you have a women's IPL,

02:46:11.280 --> 02:46:12.080
[Guest]: even if it's a 1-month tournament

02:46:12.280 --> 02:46:14.080
[Guest]: separate from the men's IPL window,

02:46:14.280 --> 02:46:16.080
[Guest]: suddenly from 2 months of visibility,

02:46:16.280 --> 02:46:17.080
[Guest]: you've got 3 months of visibility.

02:46:17.280 --> 02:46:19.080
[Guest]: I think those are the incentives that exist

02:46:19.280 --> 02:46:22.080
[Guest]: if you choose to see them,

02:46:22.280 --> 02:46:24.080
[Guest]: if you choose to look at them that way.

02:46:24.080 --> 02:46:26.880
[Amit Varma]: Yeah, no, I completely agree with you

02:46:27.080 --> 02:46:28.880
[Amit Varma]: that women's cricket in the long run

02:46:29.080 --> 02:46:31.880
[Amit Varma]: is an enticing commercial prospect as well.

02:46:32.080 --> 02:46:33.880
[Amit Varma]: The worry just is that,

02:46:34.080 --> 02:46:35.880
[Amit Varma]: from the BCCI's point of view,

02:46:36.080 --> 02:46:37.880
[Amit Varma]: the whole focus will be men's cricket, IPL.

02:46:38.080 --> 02:46:39.880
[Amit Varma]: There's just so much money there

02:46:40.080 --> 02:46:41.880
[Amit Varma]: that they may not bother about this per se.

02:46:42.080 --> 02:46:44.880
[Amit Varma]: Whereas, you know, that's kind of the worry.

02:46:45.080 --> 02:46:46.880
[Amit Varma]: So a couple of final questions.

02:46:47.080 --> 02:46:48.880
[Amit Varma]: I know I've kept you talking for a long time.

02:46:49.080 --> 02:46:51.880
[Amit Varma]: A couple of sort of final questions.

02:46:51.880 --> 02:46:54.680
[Amit Varma]: One of the subjects on which you've written and spoken passionately

02:46:54.880 --> 02:46:57.680
[Amit Varma]: is the need for a women's IPL.

02:46:57.880 --> 02:46:59.680
[Amit Varma]: Elaborate on this a bit because,

02:46:59.880 --> 02:47:01.680
[Amit Varma]: for me, when the men's IPL happened,

02:47:01.880 --> 02:47:03.680
[Amit Varma]: and I remember there were critics of it before it started,

02:47:03.880 --> 02:47:05.680
[Amit Varma]: and I wrote a long piece in Crick Info,

02:47:05.880 --> 02:47:08.680
[Amit Varma]: kind of talking about the wonders it would do,

02:47:08.880 --> 02:47:10.680
[Amit Varma]: and even I underestimated them.

02:47:10.880 --> 02:47:13.680
[Amit Varma]: But the wonders were not just in a commercial sense.

02:47:13.880 --> 02:47:15.680
[Amit Varma]: I just felt that culturally it would have a big impact

02:47:15.880 --> 02:47:18.680
[Amit Varma]: in terms of giving many more players a livelihood,

02:47:18.880 --> 02:47:20.680
[Amit Varma]: making the field much more competitive

02:47:20.680 --> 02:47:22.480
[Amit Varma]: where you don't have the monopsony of the BCCI

02:47:22.680 --> 02:47:24.480
[Amit Varma]: as the only buyer for your services.

02:47:24.680 --> 02:47:26.480
[Amit Varma]: Within this artificial environment,

02:47:26.680 --> 02:47:29.480
[Amit Varma]: you have eight people competing to get talented cricketers,

02:47:29.680 --> 02:47:31.480
[Amit Varma]: to build talented cricketers.

02:47:31.680 --> 02:47:34.480
[Amit Varma]: You know, instead of 10 people making a living from the game,

02:47:34.680 --> 02:47:38.480
[Amit Varma]: you have 100 people making that kind of living from the game.

02:47:38.680 --> 02:47:41.480
[Amit Varma]: So it just culturally, it kind of changed everything.

02:47:41.680 --> 02:47:45.480
[Amit Varma]: So tell me about what, you know, your case for a women's IPL.

02:47:45.680 --> 02:47:47.480
[Amit Varma]: Do you see a similar sort of thing happening

02:47:47.680 --> 02:47:49.480
[Amit Varma]: if it's just allowed to exist?

02:47:49.480 --> 02:47:51.280
[Amit Varma]: Because like I said, it would take a fraction

02:47:51.480 --> 02:47:53.280
[Amit Varma]: of the investment of the male IPL

02:47:53.480 --> 02:47:56.280
[Amit Varma]: and I'm pretty sure people would tune in.

02:47:57.480 --> 02:48:01.280
[Guest]: So just to finish off one point on the previous question,

02:48:01.480 --> 02:48:05.280
[Guest]: is that, you know, if the BCCI can almost have

02:48:05.480 --> 02:48:07.280
[Guest]: a focus completely on men's cricket,

02:48:07.480 --> 02:48:10.280
[Guest]: it's not outlandish to for them, you know,

02:48:10.480 --> 02:48:13.280
[Guest]: build up a dedicated women's cricket section

02:48:13.480 --> 02:48:16.280
[Guest]: and give them a budget and say,

02:48:16.480 --> 02:48:18.280
[Guest]: okay, we're not going to pay attention to you at all,

02:48:18.280 --> 02:48:20.080
[Guest]: you can do whatever you want,

02:48:20.280 --> 02:48:22.080
[Guest]: which would almost kind of be an ideal case scenario

02:48:22.280 --> 02:48:24.080
[Guest]: for many fans of women's cricket where, you know,

02:48:24.280 --> 02:48:27.080
[Guest]: you have a decision maker with some actual power

02:48:27.280 --> 02:48:29.080
[Guest]: using a budget given by the BCCI,

02:48:29.280 --> 02:48:31.080
[Guest]: which is kind of the best of both worlds.

02:48:31.280 --> 02:48:33.080
[Guest]: To come to the IPL question,

02:48:33.280 --> 02:48:37.080
[Guest]: many ways in which I think about a successful sports team

02:48:37.280 --> 02:48:41.080
[Guest]: is their value in terms of the broadcast market.

02:48:41.280 --> 02:48:44.080
[Guest]: What makes a successful sports team valuable?

02:48:44.280 --> 02:48:46.080
[Guest]: What made the Indian women's cricket team

02:48:46.080 --> 02:48:49.880
[Guest]: suddenly a subject of interest and therefore a subject of commerce

02:48:50.080 --> 02:48:52.880
[Guest]: is that performance in a World Cup.

02:48:53.080 --> 02:48:55.880
[Guest]: Again, they kind of acted up with a performance

02:48:56.080 --> 02:48:58.880
[Guest]: where they reached the final of the 2020 World Cup

02:48:59.080 --> 02:49:03.880
[Guest]: and it must be acknowledged that

02:49:04.080 --> 02:49:09.880
[Guest]: when Australia established that record of 86,174 people

02:49:10.080 --> 02:49:12.880
[Guest]: in the MCG for a women's cricket final,

02:49:12.880 --> 02:49:17.680
[Guest]: a big part of that, well, a part of that for sure

02:49:17.880 --> 02:49:19.680
[Guest]: is the fact that India were their opposition.

02:49:19.880 --> 02:49:21.680
[Guest]: If New Zealand were their opposition,

02:49:21.880 --> 02:49:24.680
[Guest]: would they have pulled in so many people? I'm not sure.

02:49:24.880 --> 02:49:28.680
[Guest]: So, which tells you that this Indian team,

02:49:28.880 --> 02:49:30.680
[Guest]: if it does well at a World Cup,

02:49:30.880 --> 02:49:34.680
[Guest]: becomes a big property, becomes a big financial property for you.

02:49:34.880 --> 02:49:37.680
[Guest]: Now, what will help the Indian team win a World Cup?

02:49:37.880 --> 02:49:40.680
[Guest]: We've seen the effect with the men's IPL

02:49:40.680 --> 02:49:43.480
[Guest]: on how it's impacted the performance,

02:49:43.680 --> 02:49:45.480
[Guest]: the international performances of the Indian team.

02:49:45.680 --> 02:49:48.480
[Guest]: That is one of the cases, that is one of the strongest cases

02:49:48.680 --> 02:49:52.480
[Guest]: for creating a women's IPL because it will help you win a World Cup.

02:49:52.680 --> 02:49:54.480
[Guest]: So, you're creating these other,

02:49:54.680 --> 02:49:57.480
[Guest]: maybe, you know, you're creating these other eight players in the system

02:49:57.680 --> 02:50:00.480
[Guest]: but it's going to help the big player get even stronger.

02:50:00.680 --> 02:50:04.480
[Guest]: One of the biggest cases where the incentives are just aligned

02:50:04.680 --> 02:50:08.480
[Guest]: to really make this absolutely happen,

02:50:08.480 --> 02:50:12.280
[Guest]: make it grow as fast as possible and make it the number one women's league in the world.

02:50:12.480 --> 02:50:16.280
[Guest]: The other impacts of the IPL, like we've seen,

02:50:16.480 --> 02:50:19.280
[Guest]: are really the human stories that come out of the men's IPL.

02:50:19.480 --> 02:50:22.280
[Guest]: Where you have someone like a Varun Chakravarthy,

02:50:22.480 --> 02:50:24.280
[Guest]: almost given up cricket, working as an architect,

02:50:24.480 --> 02:50:27.280
[Guest]: now IPL star, Indian team player.

02:50:27.480 --> 02:50:30.280
[Guest]: Within the Indian team itself, you have so many of those stories.

02:50:30.480 --> 02:50:34.280
[Guest]: You have Shikha Pandey, Air Force officer and Indian cricketer.

02:50:34.480 --> 02:50:36.280
[Guest]: You have someone like a Radha Yadav,

02:50:36.280 --> 02:50:43.080
[Guest]: whose father was a vegetable seller on literally like a footpath in Mumbai.

02:50:43.280 --> 02:50:47.080
[Guest]: And now, you know, through the money that she's earned for the Indian team,

02:50:47.280 --> 02:50:49.080
[Guest]: they're able to afford a flat in Mumbai.

02:50:49.280 --> 02:50:56.080
[Guest]: Those kind of stories and the potential for those stories to effect actual social change.

02:50:56.280 --> 02:51:00.080
[Guest]: Because you are talking about women in India.

02:51:00.280 --> 02:51:03.080
[Guest]: You are talking about a group which has its own challenges,

02:51:03.080 --> 02:51:07.880
[Guest]: own social restrictions or own social obstacles.

02:51:08.080 --> 02:51:09.880
[Guest]: And we've seen that.

02:51:10.080 --> 02:51:11.880
[Guest]: I mean, this is a concept that my brothers and I talk about.

02:51:12.080 --> 02:51:17.880
[Guest]: It's very often in a lifetime hard to jump up one's socioeconomic class.

02:51:18.080 --> 02:51:19.880
[Guest]: The class that you are almost born into.

02:51:20.080 --> 02:51:21.880
[Guest]: Cricket is a vehicle that allows that.

02:51:22.080 --> 02:51:23.880
[Guest]: Cricket is a vehicle that allows you,

02:51:24.080 --> 02:51:25.880
[Guest]: because of the popularity in the country

02:51:26.080 --> 02:51:28.880
[Guest]: and because of the money associated with the IPL, it allows that.

02:51:29.080 --> 02:51:30.880
[Guest]: And I want to hear more stories like that.

02:51:30.880 --> 02:51:33.680
[Guest]: I mean, that's my case for a women's IPL.

02:51:33.880 --> 02:51:38.680
[Guest]: I want to hear more stories where Shafali Verma was able to pay for her father

02:51:38.880 --> 02:51:40.680
[Guest]: to fly out of the country for the first time.

02:51:40.880 --> 02:51:43.680
[Guest]: He is seeing suddenly the world in a whole new light.

02:51:43.880 --> 02:51:47.680
[Guest]: That entire generation is just exposed to something completely different

02:51:47.880 --> 02:51:49.680
[Guest]: because of what she's done.

02:51:49.880 --> 02:51:54.680
[Guest]: That's the social change that I want to be effected through a women's IPL.

02:51:54.880 --> 02:51:56.680
[Amit Varma]: Final question.

02:51:56.880 --> 02:51:59.680
[Amit Varma]: You know, one way of kind of transforming women's cricket

02:51:59.680 --> 02:52:02.480
[Amit Varma]: is through top-down action of the kind we've been mentioning,

02:52:02.680 --> 02:52:04.480
[Amit Varma]: that the BCCI get its act together.

02:52:04.680 --> 02:52:06.480
[Amit Varma]: And even if they have a separate department,

02:52:06.680 --> 02:52:10.480
[Amit Varma]: I think it's kind of a little bit of luck that who will they have in charge there.

02:52:10.680 --> 02:52:13.480
[Amit Varma]: Will it be a politician or will it be someone from within the game

02:52:13.680 --> 02:52:16.480
[Amit Varma]: who really cares about it, which is kind of uncontrollable.

02:52:16.680 --> 02:52:18.480
[Amit Varma]: But I totally get it.

02:52:18.680 --> 02:52:20.480
[Amit Varma]: But one of the ways of driving that change is from the top-down.

02:52:20.680 --> 02:52:21.480
[Amit Varma]: The BCCI does things.

02:52:21.680 --> 02:52:24.480
[Amit Varma]: They put India A, all of that into place, all of that happens.

02:52:24.680 --> 02:52:27.480
[Amit Varma]: But the other is also from the bottom-up,

02:52:27.480 --> 02:52:30.280
[Amit Varma]: where there is a passion for the game that is coming from the grassroots.

02:52:30.480 --> 02:52:35.280
[Amit Varma]: More people are playing it and supply eventually meets that demand.

02:52:35.480 --> 02:52:37.280
[Amit Varma]: Now, clearly that wasn't the case,

02:52:37.480 --> 02:52:39.280
[Amit Varma]: say, even when you took up cricket,

02:52:39.480 --> 02:52:43.280
[Amit Varma]: in the sense that you point out about how so much of it is kind of happenstance,

02:52:43.480 --> 02:52:46.280
[Amit Varma]: that, you know, Shubhangi Kulkarni, Dana Edulji,

02:52:46.480 --> 02:52:49.280
[Amit Varma]: all the pieces kind of falling into place that took you wherever.

02:52:49.480 --> 02:52:52.280
[Amit Varma]: But cultural barriers, physical barriers,

02:52:52.480 --> 02:52:55.280
[Amit Varma]: like you talk in that report about how you didn't have changing rooms.

02:52:55.280 --> 02:52:58.080
[Amit Varma]: So after a, you know, gruelling session,

02:52:58.280 --> 02:53:00.080
[Amit Varma]: all the boys would just change their T-shirt and go home

02:53:00.280 --> 02:53:02.080
[Amit Varma]: and you'd be all sweaty and, you know,

02:53:02.280 --> 02:53:04.080
[Amit Varma]: you'd put on a jumper over what you were wearing

02:53:04.280 --> 02:53:08.080
[Amit Varma]: because you didn't want people in the local train to have to tolerate your sweat.

02:53:08.280 --> 02:53:12.080
[Amit Varma]: But now with the kind of the changing profile,

02:53:12.280 --> 02:53:15.080
[Amit Varma]: with the fact that people don't need to physically meet a Shubhangi Kulkarni

02:53:15.280 --> 02:53:19.080
[Amit Varma]: when they can watch a Snehal Pradhan video on YouTube and get inspired by that.

02:53:19.280 --> 02:53:22.080
[Amit Varma]: Or they can even watch, like there's a charming talk show

02:53:22.080 --> 02:53:25.880
[Amit Varma]: that Smriti Mandana and I think Jemima Rodrigues too, you know,

02:53:26.080 --> 02:53:27.880
[Amit Varma]: and they can watch that and make them role models.

02:53:28.080 --> 02:53:30.880
[Amit Varma]: So do you feel that in terms of bottoms up,

02:53:31.080 --> 02:53:32.880
[Amit Varma]: something happening there,

02:53:33.080 --> 02:53:34.880
[Amit Varma]: that at least there things are changing,

02:53:35.080 --> 02:53:37.880
[Amit Varma]: that happenstance of that sort will no longer be so rare,

02:53:38.080 --> 02:53:39.880
[Amit Varma]: will no longer be so necessary?

02:53:40.080 --> 02:53:42.880
[Amit Varma]: And just people's approaches, you know,

02:53:43.080 --> 02:53:44.880
[Amit Varma]: whereas earlier parents who loved cricket

02:53:45.080 --> 02:53:46.880
[Amit Varma]: and wanted to live vicariously through their kids

02:53:47.080 --> 02:53:48.880
[Amit Varma]: might have sent their son to a coaching camp.

02:53:49.080 --> 02:53:50.880
[Amit Varma]: Today they'll send their daughter to a coaching camp.

02:53:50.880 --> 02:53:53.680
[Amit Varma]: So what's your sense of the change actually happening

02:53:53.880 --> 02:53:56.680
[Amit Varma]: in our society in that context?

02:53:56.880 --> 02:53:58.680
[Guest]: That's a really good question.

02:53:58.880 --> 02:54:01.680
[Guest]: It's probably one that I haven't really thought about before.

02:54:01.880 --> 02:54:03.680
[Guest]: But just thinking about it right now,

02:54:03.880 --> 02:54:07.680
[Guest]: I think about it about how it exists in men's cricket

02:54:07.880 --> 02:54:10.680
[Guest]: because that is what the situation is in men's cricket

02:54:10.880 --> 02:54:15.680
[Guest]: where the demand is just so much that supply arises.

02:54:15.880 --> 02:54:17.680
[Guest]: Then, you know, there are tennis ball tournaments

02:54:17.680 --> 02:54:21.480
[Guest]: organized at every little open space you can find

02:54:21.680 --> 02:54:23.480
[Guest]: because there are people playing tennis ball cricket there

02:54:23.680 --> 02:54:25.480
[Guest]: who say, let's make a tournament.

02:54:25.680 --> 02:54:28.480
[Guest]: So can we get to that point?

02:54:28.680 --> 02:54:32.480
[Guest]: Yes, I mean, in theory, yes,

02:54:32.680 --> 02:54:35.480
[Guest]: it will take a long time for bottom up change to happen.

02:54:35.680 --> 02:54:40.480
[Guest]: It will probably take an event like how it did for India.

02:54:40.680 --> 02:54:41.480
[Guest]: If you think about, you know,

02:54:41.680 --> 02:54:44.480
[Guest]: how men's cricket's current situation has developed,

02:54:44.680 --> 02:54:46.480
[Guest]: it's been slow cooked for 30 years.

02:54:46.480 --> 02:54:49.280
[Guest]: It's been slow cooked since 1983

02:54:49.480 --> 02:54:52.280
[Guest]: throughout the entire generation of Sachin Tendulkar worship.

02:54:52.480 --> 02:54:54.280
[Guest]: Now into the generation of, you know,

02:54:54.480 --> 02:54:57.280
[Guest]: a team that can go abroad and win.

02:54:57.480 --> 02:55:01.280
[Guest]: That's the kind of time I'm talking about that it will take.

02:55:01.480 --> 02:55:04.280
[Guest]: You never know, you know, there might be an incredible event.

02:55:04.480 --> 02:55:07.280
[Guest]: We, you know, we underestimate these kind of things.

02:55:07.480 --> 02:55:09.280
[Guest]: There might be an incredible event in women's cricket

02:55:09.480 --> 02:55:12.280
[Guest]: which just drives that almost overnight,

02:55:12.480 --> 02:55:15.280
[Guest]: you know, relatively speaking overnight.

02:55:15.280 --> 02:55:19.080
[Guest]: And then you might have, like you said,

02:55:19.280 --> 02:55:22.080
[Guest]: supply suddenly turning up because there is so much demand.

02:55:22.280 --> 02:55:26.080
[Guest]: I feel there is definitely a shift in terms of

02:55:26.280 --> 02:55:31.080
[Guest]: how the likes of Smriti Mandhana are such popular figures nowadays

02:55:31.280 --> 02:55:34.080
[Guest]: and the influence that they're having on the next generation

02:55:34.280 --> 02:55:37.080
[Guest]: is probably something we'll only understand once the generation grows up.

02:55:37.280 --> 02:55:39.080
[Guest]: So it's definitely possible.

02:55:39.080 --> 02:55:44.880
[Guest]: There are so many more ways for people to get into coaching, etc.

02:55:45.080 --> 02:55:47.880
[Guest]: and start on their first few steps of the journey.

02:55:48.080 --> 02:55:52.880
[Guest]: But the next few steps are still held by these institutions

02:55:53.080 --> 02:55:56.880
[Guest]: and therefore you might have more,

02:55:57.080 --> 02:55:58.880
[Guest]: the base of the pyramid does get wider,

02:55:59.080 --> 02:56:00.880
[Guest]: but then to move up the pyramid,

02:56:01.080 --> 02:56:02.880
[Guest]: you do have to move to a few fixed ladders.

02:56:03.080 --> 02:56:06.880
[Guest]: And that's where I'm a little worried,

02:56:07.080 --> 02:56:07.880
[Guest]: a little cynical about this

02:56:07.880 --> 02:56:11.680
[Guest]: because we've already seen this since the 2017 World Cup,

02:56:11.880 --> 02:56:13.680
[Guest]: cricket academies everywhere.

02:56:13.880 --> 02:56:15.680
[Guest]: I mean, just after the 2017 World Cup,

02:56:15.880 --> 02:56:17.680
[Guest]: so many girls turned up at cricket academies,

02:56:17.880 --> 02:56:20.680
[Guest]: but they don't yet have that many tournaments

02:56:20.880 --> 02:56:23.680
[Guest]: to really fill their appetite.

02:56:23.880 --> 02:56:27.680
[Guest]: And that's, I mean, thinking back to your conversation with Nandan and Joy,

02:56:27.880 --> 02:56:30.680
[Guest]: I think Nandan was also talking about

02:56:30.880 --> 02:56:32.680
[Guest]: just creating these tournaments

02:56:32.880 --> 02:56:36.680
[Guest]: and how that really changes the ecosystem

02:56:36.680 --> 02:56:39.480
[Guest]: just by virtue of having more opportunities to play.

02:56:39.680 --> 02:56:42.480
[Guest]: I think that is where the demand already exists

02:56:42.680 --> 02:56:45.480
[Guest]: and the supply needs to step up.

02:56:45.680 --> 02:56:47.480
[Amit Varma]: Yeah, I guess it's a bit of a chicken and egg thing

02:56:47.680 --> 02:56:48.480
[Amit Varma]: where the demand exists,

02:56:48.680 --> 02:56:50.480
[Amit Varma]: but it can't express itself in any particular way

02:56:50.680 --> 02:56:51.480
[Amit Varma]: because there's no supply.

02:56:51.680 --> 02:56:52.480
[Amit Varma]: If you had tournaments,

02:56:52.680 --> 02:56:55.480
[Amit Varma]: you would know how many people are really interested.

02:56:55.680 --> 02:56:57.480
[Amit Varma]: So I guess at some point,

02:56:57.680 --> 02:57:00.480
[Amit Varma]: it's up to creative entrepreneurs

02:57:00.680 --> 02:57:02.480
[Amit Varma]: and passionate crusaders like yourself

02:57:02.680 --> 02:57:04.480
[Amit Varma]: to kind of change that.

02:57:04.480 --> 02:57:08.280
[Amit Varma]: So, you know, thanks a lot for giving me so much time on the show.

02:57:08.480 --> 02:57:09.280
[Amit Varma]: I'm really looking forward

02:57:09.480 --> 02:57:11.280
[Amit Varma]: not just to what happens in women's cricket,

02:57:11.480 --> 02:57:13.280
[Amit Varma]: but also your journey as a creator,

02:57:13.480 --> 02:57:15.280
[Amit Varma]: which is, I think, just so inspiring

02:57:15.480 --> 02:57:18.280
[Amit Varma]: in terms of the kind of output you put out.

02:57:18.480 --> 02:57:20.280
[Amit Varma]: And I'm going to go and watch that video again

02:57:20.480 --> 02:57:22.280
[Amit Varma]: to kind of hit myself with it

02:57:22.480 --> 02:57:24.280
[Amit Varma]: and say, look how much she does in a day, you fool.

02:57:24.480 --> 02:57:25.280
[Amit Varma]: What are you doing?

02:57:25.480 --> 02:57:27.280
[Amit Varma]: So thanks so much, Snehal.

